title: layered salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite-size pieces and place in a large salad bowl.
Add a layer of each one of the ingredients.
Mix 1 1/2 cups salad dressing with 2 tablespoons sugar and spread on top. Sprinkle 1 cup shredded sharp Cheddar cheese on top of dressing mixture.
Add 8 strips of crisp bacon crumbled on top of cheese.

title: corn chowder soup
directions: *Recipe calls for bacon, but we found we also like to use smoked sausage in place of the bacon for a change.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Pound chicken breasts between waxed paper to flatten.
Lightly butter chicken breasts with mayonnaise.
Season with salt and pepper, as desired.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Carefully turn breasts and repeat on other side.
Heat a large skillet over medium heat; add olive oil and butter.
Cook breasts for 3 minutes.
Turn and continue cooking for about 2 minutes.
Spoon about 2 to 3 tablespoons of spaghetti sauce over each breast and sprinkle with cheese.
Turn heat to low; cover skillet and cook for 1 more minute or until done.

title: crunchy cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until set. Makes 12 servings.

title: gingered melon and grape salad
directions: Wash and scrub melons and other fruit.
Cut melons, cantaloupes and grapes in half.
Seed, peel and cut melon into 1-inch chunks.
Toss all ingredients in a large serving bowl to mix.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve or up to 8 hours.

title: california casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine onion, rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, salt, pepper, chiles and 1 1/2 cups cheese. Pour mixture into 3-quart baking dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: holiday fruit ball
directions: Combine margarine, marshmallows and milk in a sauce pan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Combine cracker crumbs, fruit and nuts in a large mixing bowl.
Add milk mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Form into 1 1/2 inch balls. Roll in coconut.

title: cabbage and noodles(makes 4 servings)
directions: Bring 3 quarts water to boil in large pot.
Add cabbage and noodles and return to boil.
Boil 6 to 8 minutes until both are tender.
Remove from heat and reserve 3/4 cup cooking liquid. Pour cabbage-noodle mixture in colander to drain.
Return reserved cooking liquid to pot.
Add butter, poppy seed, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat until butter melts.
Add cabbage and noodles and toss to mix and coat.
Serve immediately.

title: chilies rellenos
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Beat egg whites in a separate bowl until stiff peaks form.
Fold beaten egg whites into egg yolks.
Sift in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well gently.
Combine onion, Cheddar cheese and stuffed canned chillies.
Dip in batter, coating well.
Fry in oil until brown on all sides, turning once.
Drain and serve.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing; don't let stand. Spoon stuffing across center of 2-quart, shallow baking dish. Arrange 3 chicken pieces on each side of stuffing, overlapping if necessary.

title: layered chef salad
directions: Cook barley in boiling salted water, covered, 10 to 12 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Drain and cool.
Arrange layer of lettuce, ham, green pepper, barley and celery in 3-quart salad bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard, sugar and dill weed. Mix well.
Spoon mayonnaise-dill mixture on top of lettuce layer, spreading to edges of bowl.
Sprinkle cheese and green onion over mayonnaise.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss salad just before serving.
Great for buffet or Sunday night supper!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli and melted Cheez Whiz with 4 tablespoons margarine.
Crush crackers and mix with 4 tablespoons margarine. Put broccoli and cheese in baking dish.
Put cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick chocolate pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars.
Cool and fold into 9 ounce container Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and chill before serving.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Put sugar, syrup and water in pan over low heat.
Stir only until sugar dissolved.
Cook until soft ball in cold water or 236° to 238°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Continue beating; pour in 1/2 of the syrup slowly over egg whites.
Cook rest of syrup until hard-ball (280°); add to syrup vanilla.
Beat candy until thick enough to drop by spoonful on buttered platter.

title: spoon bread
directions: Cook cornmeal and 2 cups milk until consistency of mush. Remove from heat.
Add salt, baking powder, shortening and 1 cup milk.
Add egg yolks and fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased 2 quart baking dish at 325° for one hour.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Blend brown sugar and oil until smooth.
Add egg, buttermilk and vanilla, then add dry ingredients.
Fold in rhubarb and nuts. Pour into 1 large or 2 small pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar, peanut butter and vanilla. Form into small balls and refrigerate overnight.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Stick a toothpick in the candy ball and dip into chocolate mixture.
Leave part of the ball uncovered to resemble a buckeye.
This candy can be frozen. Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk and sugar in pan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Test to be sure it forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow.
Stir until glossiness starts to disappear and is still of pouring consistency.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: brown sugar whoopie pies
directions: Blend sugar and eggs together, then add melted margarine.
Add boiling water, soda and vanilla.
Last, add flour gradually; mix until well blended.
Bake on insulated pans for about 15 minutes at 400° or uninsulated pans at 375°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix by hand the flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine egg, milk, vanilla and oil. Add to flour mixture.
Mix until moistened. Do not overmix!
Very gently mix sugar, lemon peel, nutmeg and berries. Fold into batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. While warm, dip muffin top into melted butter, then in sugar.

title: make ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 9 x 12 inch pan. Cover and refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pasta with shrimp, asparagus and basil
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, prepare spaghetti and drain. Process in food processor the basil, garlic, lemon juice, olive oil and salt until smooth. Spray nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Over medium heat, cook asparagus, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes until almost tender-crisp.
Add shrimp and red pepper and cook, stirring frequently, until shrimp are pink (about 4 minutes).
In a large serving bowl, toss pasta with basil mixture. Stir in shrimp and asparagus.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil and milk; stir until all dry ingredients are wet.
Divide and roll between floured wax paper. This recipe will only make enough for a 9-inch double pie crust.

title: easy time holiday squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
At low speed, add flour and vanilla.
Pour batter into well-greased cookie sheet.
Mark off twenty squares, placing 1 tablespoon of pie filling in center of each.
While warm, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Marinate shrimp in lemon juice, chili powder, cumin and pepper; toss several times together for 20 minutes.

title: christmas cream
directions: Combine all ingredients until well mixed.
Pour into 2-quart shallow casserole dish or mold.
Freeze overnight.
Stand at room temperature 15 to 20 minutes before cutting or unmolding.
Cut into 8 or 10 squares or slices.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: italian stew
directions: Mix all together in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Turn heat down to medium and add approximately 1 quarter size (8 ounce box) dry spaghetti, broken into small pieces.
Cook until spaghetti is tender and done.
Serve with small pieces of Mozzarella cheese on top of each serving or use Parmesan cheese on top.

title: bagels
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt and 1 1/4 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled, about 15 minutes.
Punch dough down; divide into 8 equal parts.
Roll each into a 6-inch rope. Moisten ends with water and pinch to form bagel or shape into a ball and punch a hole in center.
Let rest 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Heat 2 quarts of water to boiling.
Reduce heat and boil 4 bagels at a time.
Simmer 7 minutes, turning once.
Drain on towel.
Bake on greased baking sheet until brown, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Put baking soda, flour, salt, cinnamon and sugar together in a bowl.
Mix.
Make a hole in the center and put in strawberries, oil and eggs.
Mix by hand and put in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together (add chocolate chips last).
Pour into Bundt pan that is lightly greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool about 20 minutes.
Loosen sides of cake and turn onto plate.

title: quick taco casserole
directions: Brown beef with onions, salt, pepper and taco seasoning. Crush 2/3 of the chips on the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add beef mixture and half of the cheese (4 ounces).
Spread sour cream on top of cheese.
Layer remaining cheese on top.
Finish the layers with remaining chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with lettuce and tomatoes, if desired.
Serve with additional sour cream and taco sauce, if desired.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together and serve with crackers or chips.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Pour mixture over asparagus and marinate in refrigerator several hours.
Serve cold.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Put butter in skillet.
Melt slowly.
Add flour; let thicken. Add evaporated milk; thicken a little more, then add everything else except the fettuccine.
Use sauce as a topping; don't mix together.
Allow individual servings to apply topping to help keep it warm.

title: ashley's savory pot roast
directions: Rub pepper over roast.
Mix all other ingredients; pour over roast.
Cook in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours on low or for 3 to 4 hours on high.

title: come on over cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush crackers.
Mix with nuts and baking powder.
Beat egg whites, sugar and vanilla.
Fold crackers mixture into egg whites and bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Roll meat in flour, which has been mixed with salt and pepper. Brown well in hot oil.
Add tomato sauce, water and wine.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add mustard, onions and carrots.
Simmer 20 minutes longer.
Pour meat and vegetable mixture into casserole and top with biscuits.
Sprinkle with cheese, sesame seed or chives. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Cook shrimp in butter and sherry; save liquid (about 3/4 cup). Dissolve gelatin and microwave.
Beat cream cheese until softened and add gelatin.
Add remaining ingredients, chopped in food processor.
Pour into mold, sprayed with Pam.
Chill 1 hour. Serves 25.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and shortening.
Add water. Roll into balls and flatten with floured rolling pin.
Brown in hot skillet.

title: knorr classic spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt butter in medium pan; add brown sugar.
Mix and cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix. Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350° in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: lemon squares
directions: In a smal mixer bowl beat butter or margarine until softened. Add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until fluffy.
Stir in 1 cup flour. Press dough onto the bottom of a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in the mixer bowl beat eggs.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, lemon peel, lemon juice and baking powder.
Beat about 3 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Pour the lemon mixture over the baked layer. Return to the 350° oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until edges are light golden brown and center is set.
Cool.
If desired, sift powdered sugar over cookies.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16.

title: ice cream(2-quart freezer)
directions: Beat eggs very, very well.
Add sugar and salt.
Beat several minutes until fluffy and sugar is dissolved (beating really well is most important).
Add whipping cream, half and half and vanilla.
Beat several minutes.
Pour in freezer container.
Fill with milk to about 1/2 inch below fill line.
May use electric or hand freezer.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Blend margarine and cheese.
Stir in flour, Rice Krispies and pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls and press with fork a little. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: picnic potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes;
place in a large saucepan or kettle and cover with water.
Bring to a boil;
cook until tender. Drain and transfer to a large bowl;
mash (do not add milk, butter or seasoning).
Add salad dressing and mix well.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and half of the bacon.
Spread evenly into a greased 13x9x2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with chives and remaining bacon.
Bake uncovered, at 350°F. for 20 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off excess fat. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Stir in cream of mushroom soup and sour cream. Add mushrooms and let simmer for a few minutes.

title: easy creamy lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk, ReaLemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.

title: down-south cheese grits(yield:  6 to 8 servings)
directions: Bring water to boil in large saucepan; add salt.
Gradually stir in grits and cook, stirring occasionally, for 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in slightly beaten eggs, 1 cup of shredded Cheddar cheese, milk, butter and peppers.
Pour mixture into a buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of shredded Cheddar cheese over top of casserole.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 1 hour or until top is golden and casserole is bubbly.

title: hungry jack dinner
directions: Mix all together except biscuits and 1 cup grated cheese.
Put into casserole dish.
Cook at 350° in oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove from oven, cut biscuits in half, place on top of mixture, sprinkle 1 cup remaining cheese, return to oven and bake until biscuits are light brown.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine the vegetables, salt and sugar and cook until the mixture comes to a boil; cook until thick.
Put vinegar, sugar and spices last.
Put in 350° oven.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Thaw pie crusts.
Make sure they are smooth and round. Sprinkle lightly with flour, if sticky.
Sprinkle 9-inch pie pan with granular sugar.
Place pie crust in pan.
Sprinkle again with sugar.
Add 1 can of apples.
Sprinkle generously with granular sugar and cinnamon.
Add 2nd can of apples.
Sprinkle again generously with sugar and cinnamon.
Place top crust on top.
Pinch edges and mark center with a knife for steam vent.
Cover all edges with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes, until browned.
Remove foil and serve warm or cold.

title: party celery snack
directions: Swirl together cream cheese and raspberry jam.
Put on fresh celery stems.
Top with honey roasted nuts.
Great for showers or wedding receptions.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In medium saucepan, combine the water, undrained tomatoes, bouillon, basil and oregano.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in frozen vegetables and tortellini.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 7 minutes or until tortellini are tender. Stir in parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Wash rice.
Mix soup with rice.
Add 2 cans of water, salt and pepper.
Season pork chops.
Pour mixture in dish.
Lay pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 10 minutes or until brown on top.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Soften cookie dough and press into a round pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Let cool.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla in bowl until light and fluffy. Add mixture of flour, cocoa, soda and salt alternately with 1/4 cup milk, mixing well after each addition. Chill for 20 minutes. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool for 1 minute.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, sugar, vanilla, oil and eggs together.
Add flour, soda and salt in first mixture.
Fold in oats, then corn flakes.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Saute onions in butter.
Add all ingredients except mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Simmer on low heat until cheese is melted.
Add mushrooms and chestnuts.
Serve in chafing dish with Fritos or crackers.
May be turned into casserole by putting broccoli mixture into casserole dish, topping with buttered bread or cracker crumbs and baked until bubbly.

title: apple butter(oven method)
directions: Bake 3 hours at 350°.
Stir occasionally.
Put into jars and seal.
Add 1 cup crushed pineapple, if desired.
Makes 10 pints.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat in order given.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: lemon seven-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding and oil.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each egg.
Add 7-Up.
Pour into extra large rectangle pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spiced cranberry-orange mold
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice and spices.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in orange and spoon into 5 cup mold which has been lightly sprayed with Pam.
Chill until firm.

title: lemon pie
directions: Pour milk in bowl.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Slowly add lemon juice to mixture.
Let set 5 minutes before pouring into crust. Top with whipped topping.

title: party pecan ball cookies
directions: Cream 1/4 cup confectioners sugar and butter until smooth. Add vanilla; blend well.
Add flour and salt; blend well.
Stir in pecans.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 baking sheets.
Shape dough into 1/2-inch balls.
Place on prepared baking sheets.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from baking sheets.
Carefully roll each ball in remaining cup confectioners sugar to coat.
Cool on wire racks.
Roll again in confectioners sugar.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: hearty chicken casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients except crumbs together with blended soup mixture.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings. Each serving equals 3 low-fat meat, 2 starch.
Calories: 310.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix eggs alone for 1 minute.
Slowly add sugar; beat on low for 4 minutes.
Add pumpkin; scrape bowl well.
Combine all dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture, mix for 1 minute.
Line jelly roll pan (cookie sheet) with waxed paper and grease the paper generously.
Pour mix into pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°. Turn cake onto towel that has been sprinkled with confectioners sugar; remove wax paper.
Roll cake and towel up together.
Cool completely.

title: christmas tortilla roll-up
directions: Mix ingredients together well. Refrigerate. Spread on tortilla; then roll tortilla up. Slice into 1-inch pieces.

title: bullseye
directions: Mix cream cheese and picante sauce together until smooth. Spread on bottom of round platter. Pile olives in center of platter.
Then make it look like a bullseye by circling the remaining ingredients out from center (tomatoes, green onion, cheese and lettuce).
Use chips for dipping.

title: three cheese ravioli with fennel sausage and broccoli rabe(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Knead ingredients together until they form a ball.
Let sit covered for 1/2 hour. Cut and roll into sheets.

title: shortbread
directions: Knead by hand until it falls off your hands.
Roll out and cut in 2 x 1-inch strips.
Prick with fork.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Turn down to 250°; check every 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt thoroughly, add to slightly beaten eggs.
Add melted margarine.
Add syrup and nuts.
Mix well, pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°, then reduce to 350° and bake another 50 minutes.
This is a mild flavored recipe.

title: pepperoni casserole
directions: Boil shells until tender and drain.
Combine shells, sauce, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese, pepperoni and 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Mix together and pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella on top of mixture and garnish with slices of pepperoni.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef in potato shells
directions: Wash potatoes; prick skins and bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Heat oven to 475°.
Cut potatoes lengthwise into halves. Scoop out potatoes, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Brush inside and outside shells with margarine.
Place shells outside up on a cookie sheet and bake, uncovered, until edges are brown (15 to 20 minutes).

title: stromboli
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt; blend.
Heat water, milk and oil until warm.
Add egg and warm liquid to flour mixture.
Blend well.
Add remaining 1 3/4 cups flour.
Knead about 5 minutes until smooth and pliable.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Roll out into rectangular shape and layer with filling.

title: dill bread
directions: Mix together Parmesan cheese, margarine, garlic powder and dill weed.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Randomly place biscuit halves from 1 can; pour half of butter mixture over layer.
Randomly place biscuit halves from 2nd can.
Pour remaining butter mixture over top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until golden. Invert onto plate and let sit so seasoning drips onto rolls.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring all ingredients (except for peanut butter) to a full boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and set pan in cold water to cool.
Add peanut butter and beat until thick, then pour into buttered dish.

title: kraut relish
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: mushroom barley bean soup
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot and simmer for 1 hour.

title: mint oreo ice cream torte
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in blender.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
For second layer, heat to mix 1 stick oleo, chocolate squares, eggs and sugar.
Spread over cookie mix.
Freeze 20 to 25 minutes. Soften 1 gallon vanilla ice cream, mix in 1/4 cup creme de menthe or use chocolate mint ice cream.
Spread over frozen chocolate mix.
Crumble 5 crushed Oreo cookies on top; put in freezer.
Best when made 1 day before.

title: vanilla rice pudding
directions: Heat milk in double boiler.
Beat eggs in bowl; fold in sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in piece of butter and teaspoon of vanilla in milk.
Fold all into milk.
Add rice.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cook noodles until 1/2 done.
Drain.
Put back in pot.
Add half and half, butter, garlic, tomato sauce and broccoli.
Bring to a hard boil.
(Cream will rise to top when boiling.)
When done, stir in mushrooms.
Wait 5 minutes.
Add cheese.

title: mexican roll ups
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tortillas, in a mixing bowl. Spread mixture over tortillas, about 1/8 inch thick. Roll up tortillas. Slice into 1 inch sections. Refrigerate before serving.

title: columbus cooler punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in punch bowl.

title: yellow rice casserole(serves 6)
directions: Cook yellow rice according to directions on package.
Blend soup, sour cream and melted margarine.
Combine all ingredients except grated cheese.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch baking dish (10-inch Corning dish is perfect).
Cook for 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese and return to oven for 5 more minutes.
This is different and delicious!!!!

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Add 1/2 cup of milk to dry items.
Stir until dissolved.
Add the remaining milk and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla.
Serves 4.

title: crusty apples
directions: Peel apples; cut into eighths.
Cover the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar, the cinnamon and nutmeg; toss well.
Mix the flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and egg together to form a crumbly mixture.
Spread over apples.
Pour the melted butter over topping.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until nicely browned and apples are tender.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: strawberry pretzel salad(a dessert)
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Mix in pretzel crumbs.
Pat in lightly buttered 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Dissolve jello in boiling water; add berries at once.
Chill until almost set.
Cream sugar and cream cheese; fold in Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust.
When jellied mixture starts to set, spread over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until firm; serve on leaf of lettuce as salad or as a dessert.

title: country style steak
directions: Salt and pepper each piece of steak.
Dredge in flour; beat with mallet or saucer edge.
Saute onions in the fat, them remove onions and reserve.
Brown steaks in fat well on each side over medium heat, being careful not to overcook it.
Serve in covered dish with onions and gravy.

title: brisket
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper. Place in 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with onion. Combine ketchup, chili sauce, sugar, garlic and beer. Pour over meat. Bake at 300° for 4 hours. Cool slightly. Cut across grain. Cover with gravy from pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Place onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Pour cherries into baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon, nutmeg and 1/3 cup of the sugar over the cherries.
Mix all the ingredients together like cake batter; spoon over cherries.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 350°; bake for 15 minutes longer.
Serve plain or with cream.
It is delicious served with vanilla ice cream, also.

title: banana bread(low calorie)
directions: Grease and flour bottom of 9 x 5 inch loaf pan.

title: salmon stew
directions: Put potatoes and onion in a large saucepan and cover with water.
Boil until potatoes are soft.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chili venison
directions: Cook meat until all pinkness is gone.
Add all ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.

title: poppy seed hamwiches
directions: Mix soft butter, horseradish, mustard, chopped onion and poppy seed.
Spread on 8 slices rye bread.
Top each of 4 of the slices with a slice of ham and a slice of cheese.
Cover with remaining 4 slices of rye bread.
Place on buttered grill or heavy frying pan. Brown on both sides.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger with bell pepper.
Drain.
Add Sloppy Joe mix, catsup and barbecue sauce to desired consistency and taste.
Simmer approximately 10 minutes on low.
Add pork and beans.
Sprinkle with onion flakes.
Add brown sugar.
Simmer until ready to eat.

title: old time green bean canning
directions: Break beans and pour boiling water over them.
Let set 10 minutes and drain.
Cover with water again and add 1 cup vinegar and 1 cup sugar.
Cook 30 minutes and put in jars with 1 teaspoon of salt in bottom of quart jar.

title: fruit cocktail hot weather pies
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand and lemon juice until thick.
Add fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix again.
Pour into 2 graham cracker (or cookie) pie shells.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: Put cabbage in saucepan with boiling water, vinegar and butter.
Cover and cook slowly for 45 minutes.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Continue cooking until there is little liquid left and cabbage is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and place over medium heat.
Bring to a boil and let boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda and flavoring.
Pour over popped corn; stir to coat and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: banana nut muffins(low-fat, low sugar)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix the milk, bananas, egg whites and oil in a bowl or blender.
Add to dry ingredients and mix.

title: cheese souffle for two
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk and stir until smooth.
Add salt and cayenne pepper.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Beat egg yolks and add a small amount of the hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes after all combined.
Add cheese and let melt.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar.
Fold in mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream vegetable oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine all dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Mix creamed and dry ingredients. Add raisins and nuts and mix well.
Bake in a greased, loaf-type or tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin ice cream roll
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, pumpkin, pie spice, baking powder and salt.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes or until light yellow.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin.
Fold in dry ingredients.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients in order and mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and slice.
Serve with unsalted butter.

title: l p & l pralines
directions: Mix well the whipping cream and brown sugar; cook in microwave for 14 to 16 minutes.
Add pecans and butter.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: tina's taco soup
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat. Add water, all vegetables and seasonings, simmer on low heat until heated through. Serve with corn chips, garnish with sour cream and grated cheese.

title: red cabbage with apples
directions: Cook and stir apples in butter in Dutch oven over medium heat 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until cabbage is tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper in butter. Mix in rest of ingredients. Pour into buttered casserole. Sprinkle with 1 1/3 cups noodles on top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes with lid on and 15 minutes with lid off.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine.
Add rest of ingredients and spread in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, then rinse and drain thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in egg, butter and beer.
Beat lightly.
Dip shrimp in up to the tails and deep fry until golden brown.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Stir in sugar, oil, eggs, carrot, pineapple, the coconut and the walnuts.
Divide batter between 2 buttered and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in middle of a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until a tester comes out clean.
Cool layers 5 minutes.
Invert onto rack to cool completely.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix the above ingredients. Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Spread on crackers, sourdough, etc.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Melt margarine in large pot; stir in flour, stirring until smooth.
Add milk slowly, stir constantly until thickened.
Add potatoes and onion.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts, 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top chicken with cheese.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing. Drizzle butter over.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Yum yum!

title: spanish chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peach cake
directions: Butter and flour an 8-inch pan.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together until it spins a thread when tested.
Pour half of the mixture over the beaten egg whites. Return the syrup mixture and boil until when tested in cold water it will crackle and be brittle.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut into squares.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn in greased 17 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan.
Keep warm in 300° oven. Butter sides of 1 1/2-quart pan.
Combine sugar, margarine and corn syrup.
Cook until boiling.
Stir with wooden spoon to dissolve sugar 7 to 10 minutes.
Cook until hard ball stage, 4 minutes.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir until combined.
Pour caramel mixture over popcorn.
Stir gently to coat.
Bake in 300° oven for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Bake for 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat before adding baking soda. Turn popcorn mix onto large piece of foil.
Cool completely.
Break into small pieces.
Add nuts.

title: sunflower dill dip
directions: Mix all in blender until smooth.
Add 3 tablespoons of lemon juice.

title: foolproof rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, add sugar to lukewarm water.
Sprinkle yeast on top.
Let this stand for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baklava
directions: Stir together walnuts, sugar and ground cinnamon. Set aside. Brush bottom of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch dish with melted butter. Unfold phyllo.
Brush each phyllo sheet with butter before placing in pan.
Layer 1/4 of the sheets in pan (sheets will extend up the sides of the pan).

Sprinkle with 1/3 walnut filling mixture. Repeat layer of phyllo and walnut mixture 2 more times. Layer remaining phyllo sheets in pan, brushing each with butter first. Drizzle leftover butter over top.
Using sharp knife, cut through all layers to make diamond shaped pieces. Bake 45 minutes at 325°. In medium pan, bring sugar, honey, lemon juice, peel, cinnamon and water to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over warm, cooked baklava and cool in pan.

title: smothered wing dings
directions: Put wing dings to soak in water and salt for approximately 24 hours or overnight.
After soaking, rinse wing dings after draining salt water.
Sprinkle wing dings with black pepper and garlic powder.
Put flour in bag; shake wing dings in flour bag. Melt shortening until hot.
Place floured wing dings in hot shortening; fry until golden brown.
Drain shortening and pour 2 cups water over wing dings and let simmer with covered skillet. Simmer until it makes a gravy.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream cheese crescent bake
directions: Roll out crescent rolls. Mix cream cheese, vanilla, and sugar together. Put mixture on top of a crescent roll, top with another crescent roll. Bake at 400° until done. Prepare glaze: mix confectioners sugar and milk. Pour on top of baked crescent rolls.

title: broiled chicken breast
directions: Mix together the milk, mayonnaise and mustard.
Baste chicken breasts and broil for 5 or 6 minutes on each side, or until cooked.

title: baked pirohi
directions: Add cheese to potatoes and beat well.
Saute onions in oleo. Add 1/3 of onions to potatoes and mix and add salt to taste. Generously grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place a layer of noodles on the bottom of pan, then a layer of potatoes and repeat, ending with a layer of noodles on top.
Pour remaining onions over the top; cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix mashed sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, oleo, sweet milk and vanilla. Pour into a greased baking dish and cover with topping. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cajun shrimp pasta
directions: If using chicken, slice into thick strips.
Place shrimp (or chicken) in plastic bag with Cajun seasoning and shake to coat. Saute in butter.
Add mushrooms; saute.
Add seasonings and cream; simmer.
Meanwhile, cook linguine as directed.
Drain pasta and toss with sauce.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Very quick and tasty!

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck, then drain all grease from meat.
Add chili powder, ground cumin, paprika, dried onion flakes and granulated garlic.
Mix thoroughly.
Add tomato juice and stir until it comes to a boil, then turn on low heat and simmer for about 2 hours.
Stir frequently so chili doesn't stick to bottom.

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and cool. Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add cooled jello and mix well.
Fold whipped Milnot in gelatin mix.
Crush graham crackers; add to melted butter.
Press crackers mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add filling and sprinkle with part of crumb mix. Cut in squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: mile-high apple pie
directions: Roll one-half the pastry on floured surface into circle 1-inch larger than inverted pie pan.
Ease pastry into pan.
Combine cornstarch, Equal for Recipes, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; sprinkle over apples in large bowl and toss.
Arrange apples in pie crust. Roll remaining pastry into circle large enough to fit top of pie. Place on top of pie; seal edges, trim and flute.
Slash top crust in pattern of your choice.
Bake in preheated 425° oven until pastry is golden and apples are tender (40 to 50 minutes).
Cool on wire rack.

title: strawberry sheet cake
directions: Make yellow cake per directions on box.
Bake in 1/4 sheet cake pan and cool.
Beat together sour cream and cream cheese. Beat 2 cups milk and vanilla pudding mixes until smooth.
Mix vanilla pudding mixture with cheese mixture and spread over cake. Fold strawberries into Cool Whip.
Spread over pudding/cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with walnuts and refrigerate.

title: savory mint lamb roast
directions: Rub meat with cut clove of garlic and coat with flour, pepper and salt.
Mix sauce ingredients:
A.1., vinegar, catsup and chopped fresh mint.
Place meat in center of foil.
Brush meat with sauce and place 6-inches from glowing coals.
Roast and turn every 30 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine, chill and serve.

title: clam dip
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in frypan.
In ovenproof dish, mix remaining ingredients.
Mix together with butter mixture.
Place in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: scalloped eggplant(like a casserole; awesome!)
directions: Cook cubed eggplant in salted boiling water 15 minutes.
Drain. Add soup and milk.
Stir well.
Add egg, onion and 1 cup bread cubes.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with remaining bread cubes combined with melted butter.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake until bubbly, approximately 45 minutes.

title: charity's cracker jacks
directions: Cook the sugar, sorghum and vinegar until it spins a hair. Remove from stove and add soda and butter.
Stir and pour over salted popcorn.

title: wild rice chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
While rice is cooking, melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onion and cook over low heat until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk and chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in chicken, pimento, parsley, almonds and cooked rice.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugar pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and blend.
Alternate adding flour and milk, blending after each addition.
Add flavoring and softened margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased dish or pan. Bake at 400° until done.
Delicious cut in squares and served warm.
For variety, add your favorite topping or frosting.
My family always like sweetened canned blackberries that we all picked and I canned.

title: hot dog chili(no beans)
directions: Mix ground beef with water, enough to make it a dough-like texture or thinner.
Add chili powder, mustard and salt to taste. Place on high heat until hot.
Place on low heat; simmer for 2 hours or until done.
Dip excess grease from mixture and serve. Can be frozen.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard to a boil.
Add 1 cup oil and boil 1 minute.
Pour over cabbage and onion. Marinate for 24 hours.

title: hello dollies
directions: Place melted margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and nuts; then pour can of Eagle Brand milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool some and cut.

title: holiday cranberry punch
directions: Make syrup of sugar and water.
Combine all of the ingredients and serve over choice of sherbet.
Serves 60.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease an 8-inch round baking dish.
In baking dish, combine berries, 1/4 cup of sugar, cornstarch, 1 tablespoon of butter, lemon juice and rind and cloves.
In a small bowl, combine flour, 1/4 cup of sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in egg, milk and 2 tablespoons of butter until soft dough forms.
Drop by tablespoonful onto blueberry mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until topping is golden brown and filling bubbles. Delicious with ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: spring green onion and potato stew
directions: Cook onions, ham and potatoes for about 35 minutes.
Mix corn meal with enough water to wet.
Take a portion of the corn meal, about the size of a tennis ball, flatten in both hands and drop into onion and potato stew.
Cook another 15 minutes.

title: fried bananas
directions: Peel bananas and cut in half and then lengthwise.
Dip in beaten egg.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in shallow cooking oil. When brown, turn over and brown on other side.

title: applesauce cocoa cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla and applesauce.
Stir gently, then add dry ingredients. Stir gently.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hamburger hoagie
directions: Cook beef, bell pepper and onion until done.
Take off stove and add soup. Spread between long loaf of French bread. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and garlic salt.
Wrap in foil paper and place in oven at 450°.
Bake until cheese melts.
Slice and eat.

title: chocolate fried pies
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Roll pie dough very thin and cut in saucer size rounds.
Place 1 tablespoon of sugar and cocoa mixture in center of pie round; top with pat of butter.
Fold and crimp edges together with a fork.
Fry in cooking oil one side at a time until golden brown.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Put cabbage in freezer for 2 or 3 days.
Thaw and pull off leaves.
(It's easier than boiling.)
Combine meat, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Place tablespoon of mixture on cabbage leaf and roll.
Place cabbage rolls in saucepan and cover with sauerkraut, soup and water enough to cover rolls.
Cook over low heat.
Cooks in 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients and let sit overnight.
Next day, mix dressing and Miracle Whip.
Mix everything together and refrigerate.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Very slowly add sugar. Add vanilla, chocolate and nuts slowly.
Drop by teaspoonful on brown package paper on cookie sheet.
Put into oven and turn heat off immediately. Do not open oven door for at least 5 hours.
Just forget them!

title: onions 'n jello!
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water and cool.
Add celery, pepper, onion and pecans to cool Jell-O.
Fold in beaten cream cheese, mayo and Cool Whip.
I often omit the Cool Whip.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well. Season well. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: In a shallow greased baking dish, arrange the fillets in one layer.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
In a small saucepan, melt the butter over low heat; stir in flour, onion, salt and paprika.
Add cream and mushrooms, including liquid, in pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour over fillets; sprinkle with cheese. Bake in a preheated oven for 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lobster stuffing
directions: In skillet melt butter; add seafood salad (shredded).
Mix well.
Add bread crumbs and blend well.
(Add additional butter if too dry.)
Stuffs 3 lobsters.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix melted margarine, sugar and corn syrup with a fork.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Fold in oats.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: docona, saltfish and vegetables
directions: First, grate the potatoes in a bowl.
Grate nutmeg in bowl with potatoes.
Add sugar and raisins or currants.
Then you put all together and mix with pot spoon, not too soft; add flour to hold. Then taste to your satisfaction.
Take pot spoon to cut out in foil.
Then wrap it up or tie it up.
Drop it in pot to boil for 3/4 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Follow	directions
for
cookie dough.	Spray pizza pan with Pam. Cook until crust is light brown.
Cool.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix macaroni, margarine and cheese in greased 2-quart casserole.
Stir together eggs, salt, pepper and milk.
Stir into macaroni.
Top with more cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop and spanish rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper to taste.
Place in single layer baking dish.
Cut 6 1/2-inch rings from green peppers, discarding seeds.
Place on chops and spoon rice into and around rings.
Chop remaining green pepper and celery.
Combine with tomato sauce, water, onion, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Pour over chops and rice.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours or until rice is tender, basting rice with tomato sauce mixture 2 or 3 times.

title: chocolate nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and extract; mix well. Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in the chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat until creamy.
Add flour, milk and flavorings.
Put salt into flour.
Bake in tube pan at least 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: company potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

title: meat balls
directions: Chop all vegetables small and put in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except meat and bread.
Mix.
May add
salt, if desired.
Add meat and mix well.
Add enough bread cubes to hold meat balls together, 4 or 5 slices.
Make small balls.
Place on rack in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes, until brown.
Turn meat balls over once, halfway through cooking time.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple into 13 x 9 baking dish. Add pie filling. Add coconut. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top. Pour melted butter over cake and top with pecans. Bake at 325° until done.

title: no bake cookies (poodles)
directions: Heat butter, sugar, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Place by spoonful (medium-large) on waxed paper to cool.
If cooked the right length of time, cookies will harden.
To make cookies, peanut butter instead of chocolate, add more peanut butter and omit cocoa.

title: asparagus roll ups
directions: Trim crust from bread and roll flat. Mix cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and
mayonnaise. Spread on bread slices. Place asparagus tips on bread diagonally and roll up bread. Brush with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Add onions.
Cook with microwave for 2 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Add pineapple juice and cook 1 minute or until thick.
Stir in pineapple bits, brown sugar and ham.
Pile in center of 8-inch glass cake dish. Slice sweet potatoes 1/2-inch thick and lay around outer edge. Cover and cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Recipe yields 4 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with strawberries, apples or any kind of fruit.
It's delicious!

title: mandarin orange carrots(excellent side dish)
directions: Clean and cut carrots in julienne strips.
Cover with water and cook only crisp-tender.
Drain.
Cook butter, sugar, orange juice, nutmeg and cinnamon 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add Mandarin oranges.
Baste frequently until oranges are heated through.
Serves 12 to 16.
Serve hot or cold.

title: crepes
directions: Best if prepared 2 days prior to cooking.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Pour in miniature marshmallows.
Stir and cover.
Whip the whipping cream and add crushed pineapple, cottage cheese and crushed pecans.
Pour in jello and chill.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg yolks and applesauce.
Beat until smooth.
Then add milk alternately with flour that has been sifted 4 or 5 times with baking powder and spices.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Makes 3 layers. Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 325° about 40 minutes.
(Stew 3 apples over low heat; spread between layers.)

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Cream margarine, Crisco, brown sugar and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt; add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Bake 90 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix milk and pulp and add to flour mixture.
Add nuts, raisins and butter.
Bake in two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In shallow baking dish, combine all ingredients except shrimp. Microwave, uncovered, at High level for 4 to 5 minutes or until hot, stirring twice.
Stir shrimp into butter sauce.
Cover. Microwave at High for 5 to 7 1/2 minutes or until shrimp curl and turn pink.
Let stand, covered, 3 to 5 minutes before serving. Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli to package directions.
Do not overcook.
Drain broccoli and place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with chicken.

title: mom's best cake ever
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine cake mix, oil, eggs, mandarin oranges and butter.
Bake in 3 round prepared cake pans for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cake cool.
Mix pineapple, coconut, instant pudding and Cool Whip.
Spread between layers and top of cooled cake.

title: spanish beans
directions: Brown peppers and onions together in butter, then add other ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook beans until just tender, drain.
In oven dish, place a layer of beans, layer of sauce and layer of grated cheese.
Continue this process until beans and sauce are used.
Cover top with buttered bread crumbs and bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: penuche fudge
directions: Put sugar, cream and butter into heavy saucepan and cook until it forms a soft ball when tried in cold water (or use candy thermometer and cook to soft ball stage, 236° to 238°).

title: twin meat loaves
directions: Soak bread cubes in milk.
Add eggs; beat with rotary beater. Add meats, onion, celery, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning; mix thoroughly.
Form into 2 loaves.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine together. Add eggs and mix.
Add pumpkin and water and mix again.
Add nuts, raisins and sifted dry ingredients. Blend well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans (5). Bake at 350° for 1 hour or use smaller aluminum pans and bake approximately 40 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and add flour and milk; mix well.
Stir in eggs; add salt, pepper and corn.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Butter one side of bread slices, and place buttered side down in a 9x13 baking dish.
Spread zucchini over bread.
Sprinkle corn over squash, and then layer Ortega
chiles over corn.
Beat milk, eggs, salt and pepper together.
Pour over zucchini mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until browned.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs and canned milk with soda added to it.
Add batter to cut up fruit and nuts that have been mixed with flour.
Mix well and drop spoonfuls at a time onto cookie sheet. Bake at 320° until done.
The mixture will be very stiff. Store cookies in dry place after cooled thoroughly with wax paper between layers.

title: apple and walnut cake
directions: Blend eggs, oil and sugar.
Add flour slowly.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to blend.
Pour in prepared tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Leave in pan for 30 minutes.
Turn out; pour icing over it.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Set cream cheese out and let soften.
Place in saucepan and mash well with fork.
Add milk; place on low heat (burns easily) and mix well.
Add drained corn.
This recipe can be multiplied as needed for large amount.

title: sweet potato pecan balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans and jelly.
In a large bowl, blend well with a potato masher.
Shape into balls, using a measuring tbsp. for each.
Roll balls in ground pecans until coated.

Place on a large cookie sheet at least two inches apart. Indent top of each ball with a spoon and fill with 1/2 tsp. jelly. Bake in preheated 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until nuts are lightly toasted.
Yield, about 24 balls.

title: swiss tomatoes
directions: Slice top from tomatoes and scoop out insides, removing pulp. Sprinkle inside of tomato with salt and pepper.
Mix egg, cheese and curry.
Use mixture to stuff tomatoes.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Mix crumbs and butter and sprinkle over tops of tomatoes. Bake in a preheated hot oven at 400° for 20 minutes or until tomatoes are soft, but still hold their shape.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesy hominy casserole
directions: In a large pan, saute butter, onion and bell pepper.
Add soup, tomatoes, hominy and chili powder.
Mix together until well blended.
Pour into a large casserole.
Add Velveeta cheese; stir. Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly throughout.

title: party punch
directions: Mash berries and mix with sugar.
Add juices and chill.
At serving time, add ginger ale (7-Up).

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In blender, mix sugar, mustard and vinegar on slow.
Add oil until thick.
Add poppy seed. Good on salad greens or cabbage.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix together; roll out and cut with a cookie cutter or glass. Place on an ungreased pan.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes. Makes 12 biscuits.
One-half of this recipe makes enough biscuits to cover a casserole such as chicken pot pie.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a blender until it has whipped texture. Season with garlic powder, MSG, salt and Tabasco. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with crackers, nachos or your favorite chips.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crumple Fritos on bottom of baking dish.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco powder, salsa and chili beans.
Cook together until beans are tender.
Place the above beef mixture on top of Fritos.
Top with Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Brown in oven (around 325° to 350°) until cheese is completely melted.
Watch the cheese; it burns easily.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Boil in saucepan for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes: milk, sugar, butter and cocoa.
Pour this mixture over the remaining ingredients, in a bowl.
Add more peanut butter, as needed, to thicken batter.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls on wax paper; allow to form.
Then, ready to serve!!

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a bag; add meat and shake to coat.
Save flour mixture.
Heat oil in heavy kettle or Dutch oven.
Brown meat on all sides; remove meat. Saute onions and garlic in remaining oil.
Add meat, beef broth (blended with 1 1/2 cups water), tomatoes, salt, pepper, bay leaf and caraway seed.
Cover; simmer 2 hours, stirring constantly over low heat until thickened.
Stir in sour cream;
heat but do not boil.

title: egg yolk pastry
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cut in lard.
Place egg yolk in measuring cup and stir with fork until smooth.
Blend in enough cold water to make a scant cup full.
Sprinkle gradually over dry ingredients, toss with a fork to make a soft dough and roll out as usual. Makes pastry for three 9-inch (2 crust) pies.

title: carleta's cranberry salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together drained cranberries and sugar.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Good for several days.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large saucepan, combine strawberries and marshmallows.
Cook and stir over medium heat until marshmallows melt.

title: pancakes with cider sauce
directions: Mix and cook on griddle.

title: banana buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter and salt.
Add banana, lemon juice and sugar; beat until light and fluffy.

title: lemon cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add zest of lemon and eggs; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; alternately add flour and milk to butter mixture until smooth. Pour into 8 x 4 x 2 3/4-inch pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Prick top with fork.
Mix lemon juice and sugar; pour over top.
Leave in pan until icing sets. Remove from pan; wrap in foil.
Slice after 24 hours.

title: country steak and gravy
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Roll in flour and brown in oil in skillet.
Add seasonings.
When browned, put in crock-pot.
Mix soups and water.
Add to crock-pot.
Cook 3 to 4 hours.
Serve over rice or potatoes.

title: turkey hash, charleston style
directions: Slowly heat together the soup, mushrooms and turkey gravy or cream.
Add turkey meat.
Bring just to boiling; season to taste with condiments.
Let stand over very low heat about 15 minutes to blend flavors.
Sprinkle with finely minced parsley.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli cheese cornbread
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over melted butter. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In large microwave mixing bowl, add first 4 ingredients. Cook in microwave 8 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Will boil over if bowl isn't large enough.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well until well mixed. May have to return to microwave for 2 minute intervals until all chocolate is melted.
Add pecans, if desired.
Pour into well-buttered loaf cake pan.
Let cool.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and crumble into little pieces.
Drain and spoon beef into an 8-inch square baking pan.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.

title: cheeseburger impossible pie
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Place in greased 10-inch pie plate.
Cover with cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Blend milk, eggs and Bisquick in blender for 30 seconds and pour over cheese and meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Combine all
ingredients
in
a
large bowl.
Mix well. Put 1 tablespoon	oil into an 8-inch cast-iron skillet.
Pour batter into
skillet.
Bake
in
preheated oven at 425° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: rutabaga bake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a well greased quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add shortening, sugar, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Blend in oats.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: dessert orange cups(low calorie)
directions: Remove tops from oranges.
Scoop out and dice pulp.
Add grapes and spoon fruit back into orange shells.
Place orange cups in baking dish in small amount of water.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Five minutes before removing from oven, sprinkle flaked coconut over each orange.
Makes 4 servings.
Equals 102 calories or 2 1/2 fruit exchanges.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain and stir in sauce, onions, seasonings and salt.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes while stirring.
Place each biscuit in a greased muffin tin, pressing out to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon in meat mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: truffle cookies
directions: Cover
your
working surface with waxed paper.
Using a hand grater,
grind
all
the solid chocolate into a bowl.
Do not use an electric appliance, because the rapid action would simply melt the
chocolate.
Line
a
baking sheet with heavy aluminum foil and grease well.
In a heavy saucepan, heat the cream.
When
it begins to boil, remove from heat and add the chocolate.
Cover and
let
stand about 6 minutes.
Mix thoroughly with a
wooden spoon until the chocolate is completely melted.
Add liqueur and salt and pour onto foil.
Refrigerate until cool and chocolate starts to firm, about 30 minutes.

title: sausage pin-wheels
directions: Mix all ingredients except sausage. Roll dough 1/4 inch thick, spread with sausage; roll up like a jelly-roll. Chill and slice 1/2 inch thick. Bake in ungreased pan at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve hot with crackers.

title: amazing grace salad
directions: Drain oranges, partially drain pineapple.
Mix oranges, pineapple, sugar and sour cream.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: orange date bread
directions: Bring water, dates and orange peels to a boil.
Cook gently 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and stir in soda, oil, sugar and salt.
Add the other 1 1/2 cups of water, eggs, baking powder and flour.
Mix well.
Place batter in 3 greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together Ranch dressing and mayonnaise.
Mix all together and chill.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Split Twinkies and lay in bottom of pie plate.
Mix instant vanilla pudding mix and pour over Twinkies.
Pour any flavor of pie filling over pudding or cut up fresh fruit.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: picture window fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple, oranges, pie filling and strawberries.
Just before serving, add sliced bananas.
Better if mixed the night before or several hours ahead of time.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts; save 1/2 cup broth.
Mix peas and carrots, soups and milk.
Pick chicken off bone into bite size pieces.
Mix together with soup mixture.
Place in a baking dish. Combine Pepperidge Farm seasoning dressing with 1/2 cup broth and margarine.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer broccoli pieces. Pour uncooked rice over top.
Add chopped onion over rice.
Dot with margarine.
Mix soup and milk and pour over mixture.
Spread softened Cheez Whiz over entire dish and pierce mixture with fork until soup goes through.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in everything, but cheese and biscuits.
Heat until bubbling.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in half.
Place around top, cut side down.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat thoroughly.
Place 1/2 of crumbs in pan.
Spread butter mixture over crumbs.
Top with cherry filling.
Cover with whipped cream and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Serves 12.

title: turkey stroganoff
directions: Cook green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
In a 2-quart casserole dish blend soup, sour cream and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli bacon quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon until crisp and set aside. Beat eggs with half and half and cheese.
Stir in broccoli, salt, garlic powder and lemon pepper.
Crumble bacon.
Stir into egg mixture.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: barbecued bean bake
directions: Brown together the hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Drain. Mix in beans, ketchup, mustard and brown sugar.
Pour into a casserole dish and lay bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: black russian bundt cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix at low speed (about 1 minute).
Beat at medium speed (4 minutes).
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Let cool in pan.

title: mini pizza
directions: Separate dough and flatten.
Spoon on sauce; add pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.

title: juicy rib steaks
directions: Wash steaks; pat 1 teaspoon of cornstarch.
Wash and slice onion.
In a skillet, heat butter.
Saute onions until soft. Remove from heat and set aside.
Add steaks to hot pan.
Cook until steaks are done to your liking, 4 to 5 minutes per side for rare or 7 to 8 minutes for well done.
Remove steaks and place on platter.
Add beef broth, vinegar, thyme or rosemary and butter and stir and cook until pan juices are smooth and shiny.
Pour over steaks.
Reheat onions and top steaks.

title: fresh peaches and pears bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a small bowl.
Add nuts or dates.
In a larger bowl mix together sugars, peaches, pears, eggs, extract and oil.
Fold dry ingredients into fruit mixture. Spray and flour three 8 x 3 7/8 x 2 3/8-inch pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Test for doneness. Let cool in pans 1 hour before cutting.

title: riviera beach swordfish
directions: Preheat
broiler or prepare outdoor grill.
Season fish with salt
and
pepper.	Broil
or grill fish steaks, turning once, 20 to	25 minutes or until it flakes easily when tested with
a fork.
In
small
bowl
combine
yogurt, dry mustard, horseradish, tomato
juice
and
Worcestershire sauce.	Serve over fish. Garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Brown ground beef and onions; drain well. Combine ground beef, peas, corn, coup and water in 4 qt. baking dish. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix together all but chips and paraffin; form into walnut size balls and place on platter to chill in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and chill about 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with a fork dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on a cookie sheet; remove to a wire rack. Cool completely.
Store tightly covered.

title: no-fat macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 3 hours.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and store in an airtight container.
Put 1/3 cup of mix in 1 cup of hot water.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well.
Add marshmallows and stir.
Sprinkle jello on top.
Chill.

title: berry-banana breakfast smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; process until smooth.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Cook for 6 minutes. Stir well.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Fry bacon and put on paper towel to drain.
In bacon grease, saute next 6 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Put in a large pot and add corn, water, bouillon cubes and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add butter and milk.
Cook for 20 minutes at low heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: lizzie's pie
directions: Combine flour, margarine and 4 tablespoons of powdered sugar. sheet.
Prick dough.
Bake 20 minutes in 325° oven.
Cool.

title: sun-dried tomato pesto dip
directions: Process all ingredients in a food processor or blender until smooth.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or longer.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix honey and
vinegar
together
first, then add apple juice and grape juice.
Shake well.
Drink 3 ounces per day.

title: hawaiian stuffed apples
directions: Halve apples lengthwise.
Remove core and a bit of apple pulp. Mix peanut butter mixture and place halves back together.
Wrap securely and pack for lunch.
Makes 2 servings.

title: orange slush punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in Dutch oven; cook over high heat until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool.
Add bananas, lemon juice, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.
Break frozen mixture into large pieces; put in punch bowl.
Pour soda over and stir gently.
Makes 6 1/2 quarts.

title: dried fruit muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Combine the eggs, oil and milk and stir into the dry ingredients until just moistened.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients.
Heat all until cheese melts.
In a large casserole pan, layer torn corn tortillas with layer of meat and sauce until finished.
Use only 6 or 8 tortillas.
Heat until bubbly.
Onions may be added.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven for 350°.
Beat eggs with sugar, oil and vanilla. Stir in zucchini; mix well.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to zucchini mixture.
Stir until blended.
Spoon mixture into two greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: fondue shrimp dip
directions: Mix the softened cream cheese, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, sour cream and shrimp soup together until smooth.
Add shrimp.
Refrigerate.
Excellent dip.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Fry sausage; drain and crumble into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix well the remaining ingredients and pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 400 for 25 - 30 minutes until set and browned on top.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut up as many hot dogs in them as you want.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tomato pie
directions: Slice tomatoes and put in pie shell 1/2-inch, approximately 2 tomatoes. Put all other ingredients over tomatoes, except mayonnaise and cheese. Mix mayonnaise and cheese together and spread on top. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to 400° and bake 35 minutes.

title: holiday pecan tassies
directions: Pastry Dough:
Blend cream cheese with 1/2 c. margarine until smooth.
Add flour; blend well.
Chill for about 2 hours or overnight.
Shape into 24 one inch balls; press into 1 3/4 inch muffin cups.

title: baked chicken and rice-a-roni
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to directions 1 and 2 on package. Pour rice mixture into a 13 x 9 inch pan which has been sprayed with Pam. Place raw chicken on top of rice; sprinkle paprika on chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cook as you sleep cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Beat a few seconds longer.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Beat everything very stiff.
Fold in chips, nuts and vanilla.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Drop mixture onto foil by teaspoon.
Place into hot oven and turn off oven at once.
Leave in oven for 8 hours.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: cream caramels(christmas favorite)
directions: Use a heavy iron, aluminum or copper kettle for cooking.
Boil sugar, salt and syrup, stirring occasionally, to 245°.
Add butter and milk gradually so that mixture does not stop boiling at any time.
Cook rapidly to firm ball stage (242°).
Stir constantly as mixture becomes very thick and sticks easily at the last.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pour into a well-buttered 8 x 10-inch pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Turn onto a buttered board.
Cut with a heavy, sharp knife using a saw-like motion.
After they are cut, wrap each piece in a square of wax paper.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: savard salmon chowder
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic until tender in olive oil.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, bread and cheeses in greased 8 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Combine eggs, milk and mustard; pour over vegetable mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Before done, drizzle melted margarine over casserole and bake until done.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a skillet, cook hamburger with onion until done.
Drain off excess fat.
Add 1 can of Ro-Tel tomatoes and simmer 20 minutes. In a large pot, combine hominy, vegetables and the other can of tomatoes; simmer while hamburger mixture is simmering.
Add hamburger mixture to soup base and simmer at least 30 minutes longer.

title: corn pie
directions: Fill unbaked pie shell with sliced onion.
Add 1 tablespoon butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Add milk almost covering onions.
Mix together 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon flour; sprinkle over top of pie and bake.
Can be served hot or cold. You can also put small pieces of bacon on top of the onion before baking pie.

title: pfortchens 2
directions: Stir Cream of Wheat in milk, cook slowly for 10 minutes. Dissolve yeast in warm milk with a little sugar added.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and salt to butter.
Combine all of these items and add flour.
Stir in eggs, one by one.
Add cardamom, lemon extract and raisins.
Set in warm place to raise double in size, about 1/2 hour.
Use tablespoons always dipped in hot oil then scoop up spoonful of dough, size of small egg, and drop into deep frypan containing at least two inches of hot oil.
Deep-fry for about two minutes, when browned on one side, flip over.
Serve rolled in powdered sugar.

title: american chop suey
directions: Melt shortening; add onions and pork.
Cook on high heat until lightly browned pork.
Add rice, bouillon and sauce.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Add green peppers, celery and soy sauce, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over fried noodles.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas well and mix with egg.
Add sugar and mix.
Add melted butter.
Sift dry ingredients and add to banana mixture. Bake in greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix eggs, milk and bread together and let set.
Mix ground chuck, onion and seasonings together.
Mix well.
Add eggs, milk and bread mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Form into balls.
Put on cookie sheet in 450° oven to brown (10 minutes).
Put in roaster pan with 1 can mushroom soup and 1 can water and simmer for 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef parmigiana
directions: Combine bread crumbs and grated Parmesan cheese.
Dip steak in egg, then in bread crumb mixture.
Brown steak in oil.
Remove from skillet; put in lightly greased baking dish.
Add onion to pan drippings; saute until done.
Add tomato paste, water and spices.
Bring to boil; cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes, then pour mixture over steak.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Top with cheese and put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: clam bisque
directions: Process soups and clams.
Add milk.
Heat slowly or chill.

title: taco burgers
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning and 1 cup of water.
Stir until mixed.
Add refried beans; stir. Serve over hamburger buns.
May top with grated cheese and picante sauce.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, baking powder, salt and cheese together. Add eggs, milk, oil and broccoli; mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot souffl
directions: Cook baby carrots in salted water until tender. Drain well.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Remove bone and skin from salmon.
Mix together the salmon, beaten egg and flour.
Whip the reserved juice and baking powder together.
Pour into salmon mixture and mix well.
Dip by 1/2 teaspoon into hot grease.
Cook until brown.

title: creamy brunch punch
directions: Combine hot coffee and sugar, stirring until sugar dissolves. Chill, then combine chilled coffee with milk and vanilla.
Mix together in punch bowl.
Add spoonfuls of ice cream, stirring gently.
Top each serving with whipped cream and a sprinkle of cinnamon if desired.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts of punch.

title: grilled mushrooms
directions: Slice mushrooms and place on a large sheet of aluminum foil. Top with butter, spices, garlic and sherry or brandy.
Wrap, folding edges tightly under. Place on grill 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix chopped nuts, melted margarine, cake mix and 2 eggs.
Pour into an oblong greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix with mixer, cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour on top of cake mix; bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: apple crisp delight
directions: Peel and core apples.
Slice thin and place in a 6 x 10-inch greased baking dish.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
Mix with unbeaten egg.
This forms a crumb mixture. Spread over apples, then pour melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: "puppy chow"
directions: Pour cereal into a large bowl and set aside.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine Baker's chocolate, butter or margarine and 3 tablespoons of whipping cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted (about 10 minutes).
Remove saucepan from heat and gradually stir about 1/2 of the hot mixture into beaten egg yolk.
Return egg mixture to saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened (about 2 minutes).
Remove saucepan from heat; stir in 3 tablespoons whipping cream.
Pour mixture into small bowl and chill about 1 hour, until mixture is completely cool and smooth, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth.
