Leave in 1 1/2 cups broth. Add cream cheese to hot noodles.
Add cream of chicken soup. When cheese is melted, mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Stir well. Sprinkle with bread crumbs or cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel pop corn
directions: Cook brown sugar, butter, light Karo syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Then stir in baking soda until foamy.
Pour over popcorn.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Make a white cake.
Immediately punch holes in cake.
Pour one can of condensed milk and 1/2 can pina colada mix over it. Let set overnight.
When ready to serve, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle on frozen coconut.

title: summer salad
directions: Layer first eight ingredients as listed in a large bowl. Combine last three items and pour over cheese.
Cover tightly and set in refrigerator overnight.
Stir first before serving.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Combine tomatoes, cabbage, onions, peppers and salt.
Let set overnight.
The next day, drain and add other ingredients.
Cook 1 hour.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: orange-cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and then stir in dry jello.
Chill until serving time.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in 3 to 4-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat; cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift the flour, baking soda and spices; add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Chill dough.
Form 1-inch balls, roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix by hand and pour in lightly greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant in thin slices.
Soak in salt water. Slice onions, tomatoes and pepper very thin.
Arrange vegetables in alternate layers in greased casserole, seasoning each layer. Add melted oleo; cover and bake at 350° until done.
Last 10 minutes of baking, cover with grated cheese and breadcrumbs.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together 1/2 cup mayonnaise, milk and seasonings.
Lightly dip chicken into mayonnaise mixture. Coat well with crumbs.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Mix the other 1/2 cup mayonnaise with 1/2 cup salsa.
Use this for dipping the chicken nuggets.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender except crab meat and grated cheese.
Mix thoroughly until smooth.
Fold in crab meat.
Pour in large baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: praline cookies
directions: Boil margarine, brown sugar and pecans 2 minutes.
Do not let mixture separate.
Pour over graham crackers you have laid on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Break crackers into quarter sections.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix well, then put in 9-inch pie shell. Dot with margarine. Moisten edges of lower crust well with cold water. Transfer top crust to pie pan.
Unfold and roll top edge under lower crust, pinching top and bottom edges together (or press together with fork). Form a stand-up rim on edge
of pan to seal well and make fluting easier. Cut slits for steam to escape.
Flute edge.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 35 minutes until bubbly all over.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Allow to cool completely.
Break apart one layer of cooled cake into a large trifle bowl.
Sprinkle with Kahlua and crushed candy.
Layer with half of the prepared chocolate pudding and half of the Cool Whip.
Repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip.
I save some of the crushed candy for the top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Mix together remaining ingredients and spread over baked crust.
Top with raw vegetables.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cool carrots
directions: Scrape and slice carrots crosswise.
Boil tender in salted water.
Drain well.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over carrots. Stir.
Store in refrigerator in sealed container.
Keeps 6 weeks.

title: shrimp orleans
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Add the onion and garlic; cook until the onion is tender.
Add the soup, sour cream and catsup; mix well.
Drain the mushrooms and stir into the soup mixture. Add the shrimp and heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: no bake lemon cheese squares
directions: Arrange half of crackers in bottom of 13 x 9 pan.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in 1 cup milk.
Add remaining milk and pudding; beat 2 minutes.
Stir in 2 cups of Cool Whip. Spread half over crackers.
Add second layer of crackers.
Top with remaining pudding mixture.
Freeze 2 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes.
Garnish with pie filling (optional).

title: creamy rice pudding(an old fashioned pudding baked and stirred, with no eggs)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine all ingredients.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes. This will give the pudding a creamy texture.

title: haupia (how-pee-ah)(hawaiian coconut pudding dessert)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Pour into mold or 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Cut into 1-inch squares to serve.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Cut potatoes in small chunks.
Boil until barely tender.
Don't overcook them.
Add to hamburger meat. Add green beans and butter.
Heat for 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cream butter; stir in flour, sugar and egg yolks.
Add lemon rind, lemon juice and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add to egg yolk mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 12 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes more.
Remove from oven and serve.

title: pancakes
directions: In
medium
bowl,
combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine beaten egg, milk and melted margarine;
add all at	once to	flour mixture, stirring until batter is blended, but
still slightly lumpy.
Cook pancakes until golden brown, turning to cook other side when pancakes have a bubbly surface and slightly dry edges.
Eat with syrup.

title: drumsticks in a crock-pot
directions: Have butcher cut 1 to 2 inches off drumsticks so they can fit in the crock-pot.
Remove skin and place in crock-pot; add seasonings.
Mix soup with 1/2 can of white wine.
Pour over drumsticks, cover and let cook all day on low.
Serves 2.

title: quick coconut pie
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions and add coconut to it and shake or mix for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and red wine vinegar together well for dressing.
Toss salad and dressing about 30 minutes before serving.

title: cucumber corn salad
directions: If using fresh corn, husk silk.
With sharp knife, cut kernels from cob.
Cook corn in 1-inch boiling water for 5 to 8 minutes, until tender.
Drain and rinse under cold water; drain again. Place corn in large bowl.
Add cucumber, red pepper and onion.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except green peppers. Pour over salad and toss.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown beef and green peppers. Drain. Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil. Reduce heat. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, then serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper; add soups and let simmer.
Cut up half of the cheese in the mixture.
Cook macaroni (drain water off) and add to mixture.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with remaining half of cheese.
Put in oven and let cheese melt.

title: soupburgers
directions: Melt shortening in skillet and fry hamburger, then add remaining ingredients.
Boil together for 5 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: six-layer casserole
directions: Butter a large casserole or deep dish pie pan.
Cook broccoli and green onion in a little water with a dash of salt for 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain well.
In a bowl, combine tomato soup and half and half.

title: twin mountain coffee cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Beat eggs with milk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into greased 8-inch round cake pans. Sprinkle flaked coconut over the top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yields 16 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and chopped onion, drain well.
Add rice. Arrange
in
layers:
sausage mixture, Rice Krispies and cubed Cheddar cheese.
Mix eggs, soup and milk; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Use 13-inch glass casserole.

title: easy homemade ice cream with oreo cookies
directions: In a bowl, beat egg yolks. Stir in condensed milk, water and vanilla.
Fold in cookies and whipped cream.
Pour into aluminum foil-lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover and freeze 6 hours or until firm.

title: barbecued sausage balls
directions: Combine and brown slowly the sausage, egg and cracker crumbs. Drain; cover with the sauce mixture.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Mix pudding mixture with whipped topping. In a 9 x 13 pan, make a layer of graham crackers.
Pour half of pudding mixture on top.
Make a second layer of graham crackers and pour remaining pudding mixture on top.
Add a final layer or graham crackers and cover with chocolate syrup (not too much or it makes it overly sweet).
Chill overnight.

title: meatball chili
directions: Combine all but noodles and butter; simmer for 10 minutes. Drain noodles and add butter.
Stir gently over low heat to melt butter and coat noodles.
Serve with meatball mixture.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese together.
Add pudding to milk and mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding until all of mixture is gone.
Top with wafers.

title: economy punch
directions: Mix all together, except ginger ale.
Add chilled ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: In large baking dish or pan, layer chicken, skin side up, in single layer.
Mix together dressing, soup mix and preserves; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Serve.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken (what's left in dish).

title: kitty's corner breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Drain and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, then add sausage.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: easy berry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Pour 1/2 of flour mixture in dish.
Add berries, then remaining flour mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift together the cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Beat the eggs, add milk and shortening, stir until blended. Stir quickly into the flour mixture. Bake at 425°f. 220°c. gas mark 7 for 20-22 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup of chicken broth and oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened; turn out on a floured surface.
Form ball, roll and cut out.
Drop one at a time in the broth.
Cook until done.
Add deboned cut-up chicken.

title: low calorie dessert
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together with 3 cups water until thick and let cool completely.
Add Cool Whip and mix well. Makes about 10 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: congealed blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine juices of the blueberries and the pineapple and, if necessary, add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add the cup of juices to the gelatin mixture. Stir in the drained fruit.
Pour into a 2-quart flat pan and let stand in refrigerator until firm.

title: grandma's caramel cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Cream shortening.
Gradually add brown sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg, evaporated milk and vanilla and beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually.
Mix thoroughly.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil syrup, sugar and cream of tartar to
the soft ball stage. Add butter, vinegar and soda.
Pour over popped corn. Cool until it can be handled, then form into balls.

title: tomato basil toss
directions: Cook pasta to directions on box. DO NOT OVERCOOK. In large skillet, heat oil. Stir-fry onions and garlic for 1 minute. Add tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper. Stir and cook for 2 minutes. Toss sauce with hot pasta. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: barbeque
directions: Put onion, celery and roast in pan.
Cover with 1/2 cup to 1 cup water; cook until tender.
Add catsup and tomato sauce; cook until thick, about 1/2 hour.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: Combine mayo, sour cream, juice and salt.
Add celery, cashews and chicken.
Toss lightly and serve on lettuce.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine corn, buttermilk, oil and eggs; mix well.
Stir in cornbread mix.
Pour half of batter into a greased 9-inch square pan; sprinkle with green chiles and half of cheese.
Pour remaining half of batter over top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Cut into squares.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter, vanilla and mix well.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into a 9 inch unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle pecans over all.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
When cool, you may top with whipped cream or ice cream.... but nothing tops this.

title: dutch almond bar cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Cut in chilled margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in ice water and beaten egg.
Knead into a ball.
Press dough evenly into bottom of 9-inch square baking pan coated with vegetable spray.
Brush dough with beaten egg white.
Sprinkle glazed dough with 2 tablespoons sugar and sliced almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cut into bars.

title: perfect rhubarb
directions: Put the rhubarb in the unbaked crust of a 9-inch pie pan.
Mix flour, sugar, water, food coloring and egg well in a saucepan. Then pour over rhubarb.
Add top crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° for 40 minutes until well brown.

title: cereal refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift cake flour with baking powder and salt and add with whole wheat flour and rolled oats; mix well.
Shape into 2 rolls about 2 inches in diameter and chill in refrigerator until firm.
Slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Will make 5 dozen.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts until crumbly.
Bake approximately 15 minutes at
Cool.
Spread cream cheese mixed with sugar and 1/2
Cool
Whip over the crust.
Spread pudding (prepared by box
directions)
over mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add margarine and beat well.
Add vanilla or mace.
Add sifted flour and baking powder alternately with the milk.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt in large Tupperware bowl.
Close tightly.
Shake 1 minute or until it looks like coarse meal.
Add 6 tablespoons 7-Up and shake 1 minute or until mixed.
Roll out and place in pan.
This is a good pastry.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, put into a 13x9-inch glass baking dish sprayed with pam.
Refrigerate about 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve on platter.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break and boil spaghetti, rinse and cool.
Blend next 5 ingredients with spaghetti.
Chill and cover overnight.
Next day, mix together remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together and salt and pepper to taste.

title: layered potatoes
directions: Mix soup with onion and butter.
Layer hash browns and alternate with the rest of the ingredients.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover dish and brown the top.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cut each biscuit into quarters. Mix 3/4 cup sugar with 1 teaspoon cinnamon and roll biscuit pieces in this.
Place rolls in pan and sprinkle remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture over these.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 1/2 dollar size pieces.
Cook for 2 or 3 minutes, then drain.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour over cooked carrots and let stand overnight.
Will keep a long time in refrigerator.

title: slush aid punch
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add next four ingredients and mix well.
Freeze in plastic containers.
Take out of freezer at least an hour before serving so that it can thaw to a slush.
Add ginger ale.
Serves 50.
Also makes a great rum punch.

title: one pot dinner(crock-pot)
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off fat.

Put beef in crock-pot.	Brown bacon and onions; drain off fat.	Add to crock-pot.	Add pork and beans, kidney beans, lima beans, ketchup, brown sugar, liquid smoke, vinegar, salt and pepper to crock-pot. Stir and cover.
Cook on low for 4 to 9 hours.
If using 2-quart crock-pot, reduce recipe in half.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Flatten meat in bottom of baking dish.
Peel potatoes and slice 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick and layer over meat.
Slice onion and layer over potato layer.
Combine soup and milk together.
Pour over all layers. Salt and pepper to taste.
(You may layer any way you like, and you can add peppers, green beans, etc.)
Cook covered with foil 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: four hour beef stew
directions: Trim fat away from meat and dice into bite-sized pieces. Chop all vegetables to desired size. Mix meat, vegetables, salt, sugar, tapioca; add pepper to taste. Pour V-8 juice over ingredients, covering. Place lid on casserole dish. Bake at 275° for 4 hours. Do not uncover while baking. Easy Sunday lunch.

title: honeybun cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Pour 1/2 mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cinnamon and brown sugar; sprinkle on top. Pour over the remaining half of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Poke holes; pour glaze over the top while cake is still warm.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix and make into 3 rolls.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 250°.
Remove from oven; drain and pat dry with paper towel.
Wrap well and store in refrigerator.
May be frozen.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth 30 seconds in blender or 1 minute with mixer.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool; serve with mixed fruit.

title: marilyn's baked chicken breasts
directions: Crush bread cubes before removing from package.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Add seasoning packet and mix together.
Dump chicken soup onto dinner plate.
Coat each split breast well on both sides with soup.
Roll in dressing crumbs.
Roll up chicken breast and place in buttered casserole pan.
Repeat with all chicken breasts.
Pour melted margarine over top, coating each piece.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel sweet potatoes.
Boil until soft.
Remove potatoes from water.
Place in bowl.
Mash well.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until pie is brown.

title: poppy seed dressing(for cabbage slaw)
directions: Mix together and chill overnight (at least).
Shake up and pour over cabbage.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Roll dough out to 14-inch circle about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes or until light golden brown; cool.

title: boiled beef and horseradish
directions: The vegetables are for stock.

title: corn muffin casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, add all the ingredients and mix well. Pour mixture into well-greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Pour into well greased 9x5x4 loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake until tests done, about 50 - 60 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: beer cheese dip
directions: Warm cheese to room temperature.
Heat beer to boiling point. Add combined cheese, mustard, pepper mixture.
Beat until smooth. Serve warm or cold.
Makes 1/2 cup.
59 calories per serving.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake chocolate cake in two layers.
Follow directions on box. Only one layer will be used.
Mix pudding and milk in a bowl.

title: ladyfinger cheese cake
directions: Line a 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour half the filling in the pan.
Layer additional ladyfingers in center.
Fill with remaining filling.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix together.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Then uncover and bake 30 minutes.

title: paula's pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add in eggs one at a time, alternating with flour. Mix well.
Add whipping cream and continue mixing.
Add flavoring last and mix well. Pour in greased and floured tube or bundt pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour until brown on top.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water for 5 minutes and cool.
Beat shortening, white sugar and eggs until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients.
Combine with raisin mixture and cream mixture, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet, leaving room to flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: patrick's pizza in a blanket
directions: Roll thawed bread dough into approximately an 8 x 14-inch rectangle.
Spread pizza sauce evenly over dough.
Top with shredded cheese, pepperoni and other toppings as desired.
Don't put toppings on too thickly, because it will make it difficult to roll up.
Starting at a 14-inch side, roll up like a jelly roll. Pinch edges and ends closed.
Place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes, until brown.
Slice and enjoy.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: ham casserole
directions: Melt margarine, add flour to milk.
Add cheese and catsup; cook until thick.
Add to ham, noodles and peas.
Mix well. Spread top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves a "crowd."

title: banana split pie
directions: Spread sugar mixture over pie crust; add pineapple.
Top with sliced bananas and Cool Whip.
Put a few cherries on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: curried beef with peas
directions: Melt the butter in a skillet and add the mushrooms. Cook, stirring, until mushrooms are golden. Add the meat, salt, pepper, curry powder, coriander and pepper flakes. Break up the meat with a wooden spoon and stir all ingredients together in the skillet. Cook for 10 minutes. Add the tomato puree. Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes. Add the peas. Cover again and simmer until peas are tender, 5 to 10 minutes. Serve with rice. Yields: Four to six servings.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Boil shrimp with 2-3 bay leaves and chopped celery and pickling spice; drain.
Add above ingredients and marinate in refrigerator for 3 days.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: strawberry-rhubarb cobbler
directions: In a large bowl, sift flour, baking powder, 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Cut in 1/3 cup butter with a pastry blender or a knife and fork.
Make a well in the center and stir in 3/4 cup milk.
Stir briefly to mix, then put mixture on a floured board. Knead gently and briefly.
Set aside.

title: fried apple rings
directions: Wash, core and cut apples in 1/2 inch crosswise slices.
Melt butter in a skillet. Stir in brown sugar, spices and salt.
Saute apple rings in butter mixture over low heat, turning occasionally until tender. Serve with scrambled eggs and sausage or bacon. Makes about 12 apple rings.

title: praline-apple pie
directions: Remove plastic overwrap from pie.
Open center hole.
Cut 4 to 6 slits in top crust.
Place pie on an aluminum foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, shielding with aluminum foil after 1 hour.
Cool 1 hour.
Bring butter, brown sugar and whipping cream to a boil in a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring often.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat. Whisk in vanilla and powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour praline mixture slowly over pie, spreading to cover.
Top with pecans.

title: orange cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot orange juice.
Cool until thick and syrupy.
Chill milk.
Whip until stiff and add lemon juice.
Whip until stiff and fold into jello.
Mix cracker crumbs, sugar and butter to make crust and put into bottom of 10 x 14-inch pan.
Save a few crumbs to put on top.
(Follow package directions.)
Pour jello mix into crust and chill at least 2 hours or more.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt butter, slowly adding flour and milk.
Add bouillon and bring to a boil.
When thick, lower heat, adding chicken and vegetables.
Serve over toast.

title: cheesy lasagne roll-ups
directions: Heat margarine in saucepan.
Whisk in flour.
Gradually stir in broth, milk and basil.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in Parmesan and ham.
Steam onion until tender.
Mix onion, zucchini, carrot, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and egg whites.
Spread 1/4 cup of this mixture over each noodle. Roll up firmly.
Spread 1 cup sauce in 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Arrange rolls, seam side down, in dish.
Cover with sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 to 20 minutes more.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: old south pralines
directions: In large 3 1/2-quart heavy saucepan combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt.
Cook over high heat about 5 minutes.
Stir often and scrape bottom of pan.
Mixture will foam up.
Add butter or margarine and 2 cups pecan halves.
Over medium heat, continue cooking, stirring constantly and scraping bottom and sides of pan until candy reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and cool slightly about 2 minutes.
Beat with spoon until thick and creamy.
Drop from tablespoon onto sheet of aluminum foil or waxed paper.
Let cool.
Decorate with remaining pecan halves.
Makes about 20 (2-inch) pralines.

title: crazy hawaiian cake
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Add can of pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple evenly.
Cover with coconut.
Spoon milk over all.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve from baking dish.

title: magically moist chicken fingers
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Brush chicken with mayonnaise. Shake chicken and bread crumbs in a bag.
Bake in a 425 degree oven 15 minutes until golden brown and juice runs clear when pierced with a fork.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon margarine on the 4 halves.
Place, cut side down, in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Saute onions in 1 tablespoon butter (margarine) until tender.
Combine rice, 3/4 cup cheese and parsley.
Fill each squash half with rice mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake another 30 minutes at 350°.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Scrape carrots and slice.
Boil until fork-tender (not soft). Slice bell pepper and onion.
Don't cook.
Layer carrots, onion and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over carrots, onion and pepper.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: goober pound cake
directions: Cream oleo.
Cream cheese.
Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and peanut butter.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake 3 hours at 225°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour dressing over salad.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Blend together all dry ingredients.
Add to the liquid mixture along with zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Mix well; divide equally into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake care according to package directions.
While cake is still hot, poke holes 1/2 inch apart with long pronged fork.

Mix cream of coconut and Eagle brand and pour mixture, a little at a time, over cake until all is absorbed. Cover and cool in refrigerator until time to serve. Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle generously with coconut flakes.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Spread 1 package of crescent rolls in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Press to seal edges; set aside.
Blend cheese and sugar until light.
Add vanilla, egg yolk and raisins.
Spread over dough.
Top with second package of dough.
Brush on egg white; sprinkle nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle powdered sugar.

title: potato sweets
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let potatoes cool and peel skin off.
Cut in chunks.
Combine remaining ingredients, except the marshmallows.
Put in a square glass or aluminum pan and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Last 5 minutes, top with marshmallows and brown lightly.
Serve hot.

title: chili con queso
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in tomatoes and peppers.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Toss cheese with cornstarch.
Gradually add to saucepan, stirring until melted.
Stir in hot sauce.
Heat through.
Serve with chips. Makes 1 3/4 cups (14 servings).

title: nut balls
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy; add vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well. Stir in nuts.
Chill.
Shape into 1-inch size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: homemade tacos
directions: Saute
peppers,
onions
and
bell
pepper in oil until soft. Add
chili powder, garlic, cornstarch paste, meat, salt and pepper.
Cook
over
medium heat about 1/2 hour, stirring until thickened.
Fry
tortillas
and fill with meat mixture. Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes and shredded cheese.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Sweeten berries to taste.
Bring berries and water to a rolling boil.
Drop dough into berries by rounded teaspoonfuls. Turn heat down to a low simmer and cook for approximately 20 to 30 minutes until berries thicken.
Serve warm.

title: simple stew
directions: Stir together mushroom soup and dried onion soup mix with 1/2 cup water. Place in casserole dish with meat and vegetables. Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Dissolve marshmallows in jello water, then add rest of ingredients. Put in refrigerator to jell. Then put topping on.

title: chicken breasts in mustard sauce
directions: Saute onion and parsley in butter.
Add chicken and saute, turning once until browned on both sides, about 10 minutes. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat and cook covered about 10 minutes longer. Meanwhile, make sauce.

title: black bean and corn soup
directions: Spray crock-pot with Pam.
Pour both cans of corn into crock-pot.
Pour beans on top of corn.
Pour 1/3 of the salsa on top of corn and stir.
Place chicken on top of mixture, salt and pepper to taste; cover with remaining salsa.
Cook on high until chicken is tender (approximately 4 to 5 hours).
Spoon into bowls and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: In a separate bowl, add jello to all fruit; mix.
Pour into jello mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini easter bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg, baking powder, dates or raisins, nuts, zucchini and pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done with a toothpick.
Freezes well.

title: brown sugar brownies *
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs (one by one), then add vanilla, flour and baking powder, then the nuts.
Spread onto pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° until brown, then cool and cut in squares.

title: mercedes rolls
directions: Do this the night before making the rolls:
Combine milk, sugar and Crisco.
Heat and cool.
Mix real good the next morning.

title: spaghettios
directions: Cut onion in pieces; saute.
When done, add in ground meat in bite size pieces.
Cook until tender.
Pour in SpaghettiOs; add 1/2 can of water if needed.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes on medium. Serves 3 to 4.

title: fruit torte
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add raisins, nuts and remaining ingredients.
Stir to mix.
Bake in a greased 9-inch square pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve topped with whipped cream. Makes 6 servings.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and milk in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Arrange peach slices evenly in bottom of baking pan.
Pour melted butter over sugar mixture.
Do not stir.
Pour sugar mixture over top of peaches in the pan.
You may also sprinkle your favorite spices, like cinnamon or allspice, over the peaches before pouring the sugar mixture.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Make 2 loaves.
Brown in skillet first, then bake rather slowly, about 1 hour.

title: jalapeno-cheese corn sticks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease two 7-stick corn stick molds; heat molds for about 5 minutes.

title: garden patch hot pepper jelly
directions: Chop peppers and add to 5 cups sugar and 1 1/2 cups vinegar. Boil 3 minutes, strain and add 1 bottle Certo.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat, add 1/2 teaspoon green food coloring.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese, butter and Blue cheese at room temperature. Mix together.
Add onion powder and ripe olives.
Chill overnight.
Make into 2 balls and roll in chopped nuts.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Spread ice cream evenly in bottom of crust.
Freeze until firm. Spread caramel sauce over ice cream.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Cover with whipped topping.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 20 minutes before serving.

title: homemade lye soap
directions: Empty can of lye in water.
Stir slowly until lye is dissolved. Allow to stand until lye is completely dissolved and the water is just barely lukewarm.
(The lye heats the water.) Pour grease into large stone bowl or enamel container.
Using wooden spoon or stick, slowly stir while pouring dissolved lye mixture into grease, stirring constantly.
Stir for 15 minutes until mixture begins to get thick.
If soap thickens before time is up, pour into molds lined with wax paper.

title: chocolate pie(diet)
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Add enough crushed nuts to cover the bottom of the pan.
Cook pudding, whipping cream, water and unflavored gelatin until it boils.
Let cool.
When chocolate is cool, mix Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Slowly add cooled pudding.
Pour over nut crust and refrigerate.

title: grammie's anxiety salad
directions: Spray a large circular mold or Bundt pan with nonstick spray. Peel and cut up the oranges into bite size pieces.
Drain grapefruit sections in colander and then cut up also.
Add the fruits, celery and cranberry sauce to the walnuts in a large bowl.

title: caramel dipping sauce
directions: Mix sugars and cornstarch in pan.
Slowly add half and half and butter.
Stir constantly and bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Cook for 15 minutes or so before serving.
Sauce can be used to dip apples or place apples in dish and pour sauce over.

title: real texas chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Mix with the rest of ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.

title: bleu cheese log
directions: Blend all ingredients, except pecans, in a large bowl.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with your choice of crackers.

title: blitz kuchen(german)
directions: Mix and bake in 2 coffee cake pans.
On top sprinkle chopped nuts, cinnamon and sugar.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix with vegetables and soups.
Pour into a baking dish.
Mix the flour, milk and margarine.
Pour over the chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until the crust is brown.

title: mexican rice casserole
directions: Cook rice, salt and oregano.
In 1 1/2-quart greased casserole with cover, layer 1/2 of the rice, 1/2 sour cream, 1/2 chopped green chilies and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers.
End with cheese. Dust with paprika.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: magic pie crust dough
directions: Put all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Seal and shake for 1 minute.
Yields 2 pie crusts.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and vinegar in saucepan and bring to a rolling boil.
Drain kraut and pull apart.
Pour vinegar and sugar mixture over kraut and chill.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to kraut; chill.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, excluding boiling water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove from mixture.
Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Put popped corn in 2 large shallow pans.
Pour mixture over popped corn, mixing well. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Take out of oven every 15 minutes and stir.
Cool completely.
Break apart and store in tightly covered container (Tupperware).
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: ranch salad
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Combine lettuce, green onions, cheese and beans in bowl.
Add tomatoes and ground beef.
Pour salad dressing over salad; toss to mix well.
Serve over corn chips.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup of the cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: bread pudding(a calorie-reduced version)
directions: Spray a 1-quart casserole with nonstick spray.
Place bread cubes in the casserole.
Sprinkle with currants or raisins.
Set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, beat together egg, egg whites, skim milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour over bread and currants or raisins.
Bake in a 325° oven about 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake flour, sugar, cocoa and soda, being sure to sift flour before measuring.
Sift flour, sugar and cocoa 3 times.
Mix well, then add buttermilk, oil and egg.
Mix these ingredients well.
Add the boiling water and mix again.
Bake in a moderate oven until done.

title: easy potato salad mold
directions: Combine potatoes with celery, onion, pickles, eggs, mayonnaise and salt.
Soften gelatin in 1 tablespoon of water.
Heat pickle juice; dissolve gelatin in juice, stirring until dissolved.
Add gelatin mixture to potato salad.
Stir well to blend.
Spoon into greased mold.
Chill until firm (more flavorful if chilled overnight).
Unmold to serve.

title: iranian beef curry
directions: Brown meat in hot shortening.
Add onion and applesauce; cook until onion is tender.
Blend in flour, curry powder and nutmeg. Add beef broth and tomato sauce, raisins and brown sugar.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender; about 1 1/4 hours or bake in oven at 325°.
Serve over hot rice.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Mix rhubarb, marshmallows and 1 cup sugar. Spread in bottom of sheet cake pan.

Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cream butter and 3/4 cup sugar until fluffy. Add well beaten egg yolks. Beat well. Add flour mixture, alternating with milk, beating after each addition. Add vanilla. Beat egg whites until just stiff and gradually beat in rest of sugar. Fold lightly but thoroughly into batter.
Pour over rhubarb. Bake at 350° about 35 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let stand.
Mix the cracker crumbs, pumpkin pie spice, raisins, dates, nuts and candied fruit and syrup in a large bowl.
After mixing all dry ingredients thoroughly to ensure separation of the candied fruit, dates and raisins, add the milk mixture.
Mix until all crumbs are moistened. Press firmly into wax paper-lined loaf pan.
Chill at least 2 days to allow complete moistening and blending of flavors.
Store in refrigerator.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured layer pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs, flour, sugar, and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Remove 1 cup of dry cake mix to be used later in the topping. Mix the cake mix, oleo and 1 egg together; put into greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients together until well blended and pour over first mixture.

title: christmas cake
directions: This is not a traditional fruitcake!
Even people who hate fruitcake love this one.

title: lemony apple-bran salad
directions: In a medium size bowl, combine yogurt, sugar, lemon juice, parsley and salt. Stir in apples, celery and grapes or raisins. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just before serving, stir in Kellogg's All-Bran cereal. Serve on lettuce, if desired.

title: cheddar bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine biscuit mix and cheese.
Add milk and eggs, mixing just until moistened.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 55 minutes.
Remove from pan; serve warm.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Crust:
Mix first four ingredients.
Line two 9-inch pie pans with dough and bake for 12 minutes at 400°.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil mixture of the sugar, water, butter and vinegar until it becomes stringy, stirring constantly.
Immediately pour over popcorn and mix well. Dip hands into cold water, then form popcorn into small balls.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows until melted. Cool. Add whipped cream and pineapple.
Line pan with half of crumbs, fill with marshmallow filling, sprinkle top with remaining crushed graham crackers.
Cool several hours.

title: bacon-cheddar muffins
directions: Grease muffin cups.
Set the pan aside.

title: buttermilk pie #2
directions: Mix together.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 325° until almost firm (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Top with meringue and bake another 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix rice, water, salt, thyme, egg, onion and pepper.
Mix in hamburger.
Put 1/4 cup meat mixture in each cabbage leaf and roll up.
Mix tomato sauce, lemon juice and brown sugar; pour on top. Simmer 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: eddie's chicken sauce piquant
directions: Spray bottom of pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Fry chicken until brown.
Cover with onion.
Cover; cook about 1 minute.
Turn chicken and allow onion to brown.
Add water; cover and steam 1 minute.
Add tomato sauce, green onions and garlic.
Mix together 1/2 cup water with flour until thick; add to pot.
Add sausage; simmer for 1 hour.

title: mashed potatoes for 50
directions: Pare potatoes.
Wash and boil until tender.
Mash until smooth, using electric mixer.
Add the other ingredients.
Beat until light and fluffy.

title: mexican chili cheese dip
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cheese, chili, milk and chili powder.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until cheese is melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in tomatoes, onion and chilies.
Pour into serving dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: custard pie
directions: Warm milk to scalding.
Do not boil. Add to beaten eggs and sugar.
Pour into raw pie shell. Sprinkle nutmeg on top. Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: wild rice and mushroom stuffing
directions: Place wild rice and chicken stock in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover tightly.
Cook over low heat for about 35 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Meanwhile, cook onion and celery in butter until soft.
Add mushrooms, thyme and sage.
Cook and stir for 3 or 4 minutes.
Add mushroom mixture and parsley to cooked rice; toss lightly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked turkey
directions: Place turkey in roaster.
Add water.
Cover.
Turn oven on to 500°.
Place turkey in cold oven (not preheated).
Cook 2 hours. Turn off oven.
Leave turkey in hot oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mom's blushing peach pie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Then rub in butter or margarine.
Sprinkle half over bottom of pastry in pan.
Arrange peaches over mix.
Sprinkle with water.
Add rest of mixture. Bake in 425°
oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pet milk salad
directions: Add sugar
to pineapple and bring to a boil.
Add jello and let
cool.	Whip
chilled Pet milk and fold into pineapple mixture.
Store in refrigerator.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice first 4 ingredients into bowl; stir in Miracle Whip and salt to taste.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Chop and drain artichoke hearts.
Mix completely with mayonnaise and cheese.
Heat for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve on cocktail rye bread, sliced and toasted.

title: marinade for tomatoes
directions: Mix well.
Pour over sliced tomatoes.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and molasses thoroughly. Measure flour, blend all ingredients. Stir in and chill. Heat oven 350 degrees. Roll dough in 1 1/4 inch balls. Dip balls in sugar. Place 3 inches apart on greased pan. Sprinkle each with 2 or 3 drops of water. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or just until set, but not hard. Makes 4 doz.

title: broil-on coconut topping
directions: Combine
coconut,
sugar, butter, milk and vanilla in a bowl. Spread
on
warm
or cooled cake in pan.
Place in preheated broiler
and
broil
2 to 3 minutes or until topping is lightly browned.
Cut in squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: taco pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick and water until soft dough forms.
Pat dough in 12-inch greased pizza pan.
Mix chili, chopped green peppers and onion.
Spread over dough.
Bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and corn chips.
Bake until crust is brown and cheese is melted, approximately 5 to 10 minutes in oven that has been preheated to 425°.

title: nutty buddy yam bake
directions: Peel and cook potatoes; drain and add milk.
Beat.
Add eggs, margarine, sugar and spices.
Pour into well-greased baking dish (8 x 8-inch).
Sprinkle topping over potatoes and dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff in baked potatoes
directions: Heat olive oil and saute onion and mushrooms until tender and wilted.
Add beef and stir until beef loses its red color. Sprinkle with flour.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, cornmeal, salt and baking powder.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Stir until smooth.
Turn into greased pan, skillet or muffin tins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Add flour, cornmeal, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add Wesson oil and pumpkin; blend. Sift together dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into a 10-inch angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let cool in pan, then remove and ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: ice cream crunch
directions: Mix pecans, oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and margarine well. Bake in a 350° oven on cookie sheet about 30 minutes.
Stir often. Stir cool.
Spread 1/2 on 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat in soft ice cream.
Pour topping over ice cream.
Top with rest of crumbs. Top with Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: zesty black-eyed peas
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl, tossing gently. Cover and chill at least 8 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain mixture and spoon into a lettuce-lined bowl.
Garnish with bacon and onions.
Serves 8.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Mix chicken, soup, vegetables, milk, and parsley in a medium bowl.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with 1 crust; add filling.
Top with another crust.
Fold edges under and crimp.
Cut 4 slits in top to vent.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until pastry is golden brown and filling is hot.
tags: cream of chicken soup with herbs

title: nacho chili dip
directions: Mix chili and salsa in to softened cream cheese. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake on 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eb's quiche
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add beaten eggs, milk, butter and onion, blending well.
Fold in cheese and chopped spinach, mixing well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook first five ingredients until thick, stirring all the time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: fettucine
directions: Saute mushrooms in 1/2 stick butter.
Add zucchini, cream and 1 stick butter.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Add cooked fettucine, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
(Recipe makes a lot of sauce; you can double the amount of pasta and still have plenty of the vegetables to toss with it.)

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute the onion and mushrooms in the oleo. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add dry ingredients to melted margarine.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except crumbs in a mixing bowl. Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs or potato chips on the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and serve.

title: spicy beef rice casserole
directions: Place beef and green pepper in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on high for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir once or twice during cooking to break beef into small bits.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to taste.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cheddar cheese, together in oven dish.
Top with Cheddar.
Heat in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or microwave for 5 minutes.
Serve with crackers or Doritos to dip.

title: shortnin' bread
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon and nutmeg in a large bowl; mix well and set aside.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk; stir well and set aside.
Combine butter or margarine and molasses in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir in buttermilk mixture and egg.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in skillet 10 minutes.
Invert cake onto plate; cut in wedges to serve.
Makes 8 servings.
Made in a skillet.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Cream together softened cream cheese, Jell-O, sugar and vanilla. Dissolve with 1 cup boiling water. Stir until cream cheese has melted. Add crushed pineapple, nuts and 7-Up. Chill in mold or pretty bowl.

title: orange whip
directions: Mix together Jell-O, pineapple and water.
Bring to a boil and let cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.

title: mexican candy
directions: Cook brown sugar, white sugar, milk and corn syrup until soft. To test, drop some in a cup of water and if it holds its shape, it is done.
Add pecans and vanilla and beat until it changes color.
Drop by spoon on waxed paper.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips; dust with flour and pepper.
In a large skillet brown meat in butter.
Add drained mushrooms, onion and garlic; brown lightly.
Stir in beef broth.
Cover and cook 1 hour, stirring now and then.
Gradually stir in sour cream; cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix sugar and berries and let stand for several hours.
Add jello to water and dissolve.
Stir in orange juice and other ingredients.
Pour into mold.

title: cereal treats
directions: Melt butter and marshmallow in a saucepan.
Add cereal.
Place in a 13x9-inch pan and spread evenly.
Place in the refrigerator until cool.

title: gushy gooey bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together cake mix, 1 egg and margarine.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a medium bowl, mix together cream cheese, confectioners sugar, 2 eggs and vanilla.
Pour over mixture.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.
Best if stored in refrigerator.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute bacon in a large frying pan until just starting to crisp. Add rice, onion and pepper.
Stir constantly, about 10 minutes or until rice is hot.
Stir in soy sauce and add beaten eggs.
Cook 5 minutes or longer until eggs are cooked, tossing lightly with a fork.
Add either shrimp, beef or pork which has already been heated.

title: crab soup
directions: Melt 1/4 cup of butter. Add green onions and saute for 15 minutes. Add all other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes. Do not allow mixture to boil.

title: cheese and dill muffins
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease twelve 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch muffin cups.
Mix all ingredients until soft dough forms.
Drop dough by spoonfuls into muffin cups.
Bake until muffins are light brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1 1/2-inch muffin tins.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs and mix well.
Blend in the sweet potatoes.
Sift the flour with the baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add alternately with the milk.
Do not overmix.
Fold in the nuts and raisins.
Fill the greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.
These muffins freeze well.

title: fettucine carbonara
directions: Saute bacon.
Drain and crumble.
Cook and drain fettucine. Place in warm serving dish.
Add bacon, butter, cream, cheese, eggs and parsley.
Toss and serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together.
Add noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: martha's 5 minute fudge
directions: Mix ingredients in a heavy saucepan, stirring constantly over medium heat to a boil. Mix will bubble on top.
Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Move off heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces and vanilla (pecans, optional).
Spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into 30 pieces.

title: pudding
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Slowly stir in milk a little at a time.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until boiling.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Combine unbeaten egg white and sugar in a small 1-quart bowl. Mix well until all sugar is dissolved.
Stir in, one at a time, the other dry ingredients.
Then beat until well blended.

title: russian borscht
directions: Put water to boil in large pot.
Add 1/2 cup canned tomatoes. When water is boiling, drop in potatoes, carrots and beet.
While this is cooking, add 3 Tbsp. butter in frying pan.
When melted, add onion.
Cook until tender but not brown.
Add 3 cups tomatoes and let simmer with onion and butter until a thick sauce.
Set to back of stove.
Into a separate frying pan, put 2-3 Tbsp. butter to melt.
Add 2 cups cabbage and fry.
Cook tender but do not brown. When potatoes are tender, remove them to a bowl.
Add 2 Tbsp. butter.
Mush well, then add 3/4 cup sweet cream and mix well.
Set aside.
Add 1-1/2 cups potatoes to stock and the remainder of the cabbage.
When potatoes are done, add the onion-tomato-sauce.
Then add the cooked cabbage and the potato-cream mixture.
Add 3 Tbsp. to the borscht.
Stir well.
Add fresh green pepper.
Add 3 Tbsp. dill.
The more fresh dill the better the flavor.
Remove beet, one hour later after borscht is ready.
Borscht is ready to serve. Serve hot.
Serve with chopped garlic in your bowl and a piece of bread and butter.

title: friendship bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.

title: sugar-coated popcorn
directions: Suggestion:
Choose color of food coloring to correspond with the colors of the holidays.
Example:
Red and green for Christmas.

title: cream of zucchini soup
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in 2 tablespoons butter and garlic to taste in a small amount of water until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Puree in blender.
In another bowl, make white sauce consisting of butter, flour, evaporated milk and chicken stock. Add the puree to the white sauce.
Heat until ready to serve.

title: german potatoes
directions: Fry bacon and drain grease off.
Reserve 3 tablespoons bacon drippings and let cool thoroughly.
Boil potatoes and drain water; set aside.
In small mixing bowl, mix the mayonnaise, garlic powder, pepper, cooled bacon drippings and salt.
Crumble fried bacon and add 3/4 of it to mixture.
Stir mixture into the potatoes and top with the remaining bacon pieces.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Use a large microwave-safe bowl.
Mix box of powdered sugar and 1/2 cup of cocoa.
Make a well or hole and place stick of butter and 1/4 cup milk in the hole.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir well to blend.
Add 1 tablespoon vanilla and walnuts.
Stir well.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Pour into lightly buttered shallow pan and cool completely.
Cut into bite-size pieces and store in an airtight container.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix rhubarb, flour, sugar and egg.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cake mix and crumble.
Top cake mix with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients except pie shell. Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer.
Cool.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: lemon lush
directions: Prepare pudding, using milk.
Pour over cheese layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Sift sugar, baking powder, salt and flour together.
Add corn and eggs.
Pepper to taste.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Pour in corn mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix well the butter/margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs, 2 at a time.
Add Carnation milk, 1/3 at a time.
Add flour, vanilla, lemon, sherry and rum.
Place in a tube pan.
Place in cold oven and put on 350°.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: buttered vegetables
directions: Cut carrots and celery into bite size pieces. Cook 10 minutes. Cut cabbage and add to mixture. Cook another 10 minutes. Add tomatoes, onion, limas and peas.
Cook until done. Add yellow and green string beans and butter.
Start with 2 quarts of water and add more, if necessary.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container.
Add chicken wings and marinate in refrigerator for at least 3 to 4 hours.
For best flavor marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then turn wings and continue to bake for 15 minutes at 425°.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In large kettle, cook and stir bacon and onion until onion is tender.
Drain clams, reserving liquor.
Add clam liquor, potatoes and water to onion and bacon.
Simmer until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Just before serving, add clams, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute onions, peppers and mushrooms
(if
you use) with ground beef.
Saute until brown and
add
pizza
sauce.
Place this mixture in an 8-inch square pan
or round dish.
Sprinkle cheese for second layer.

title: pickles (refrigerator)
directions: Boil first four ingredients and set aside to cool.
Slice cucumbers, garlic and onion; pour mixture over cucumbers and let stand for 3 days before eating.
Will stay in refrigerator for weeks.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased square pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Can be served with chicken sauce.

title: appetizer ham ball
directions: Blend deviled ham, olives, mustard and hot pepper sauce.
Form in ball on serving dish; chill.
Combine cream cheese and milk; frost ball with mixture.
Chill.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.
Display with crackers.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and dice chicken.
Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with cooked broccoli and rice that have been mixed together.
Pour soup over mixture and sprinkle on stuffing. Drizzle melted oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Drain shrimp and chill. Chill egg.
Line bowl with chilled lettuce leaves. Fill with mixture of shrimp and celery.
Cover with mayonnaise. Garnish with egg wedges. Serves 4.

title: delicious meatballs and sauce
directions: Prepare meatballs and roll them the size of a thumb.
Bake them at 300° for approximately 20 minutes until done.

title: hobo's supper
directions: Season onions and potatoes with salt and pepper.
Place onions and potatoes on a square foot greased foil.
Lay hamburger patty on top.
Season hamburger.
Seal foil tightly and cook in 325° oven for at least 1 1/2 hours.
Yield: individual serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef in a large skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Add garlic and 1/2 teaspoon salt; simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: man overboard
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, celery and salt and pepper.
Drain off grease.
Place sliced potatoes in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish that has been buttered.
Spread hamburger mixture over potatoes.
Drain beans and pour over hamburger mixture.
Mix soup with 1/2 can water and pour over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for an hour. During the last 5 to 6 minutes, sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: double boiler fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in double boiler top. With electric mixer at high speed, beat about 1 minute to blend.
Place over rapidly boiling water and beat until mixture holds a peak when beater is raised.

Remove from boiling water. Add vanilla and continue to beat until mixture is stiff enough to spread. Fills and frosts top and sides of two 8-inch or 9-inch layers or a 9 x 9 x 2 or 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender. Drain off water.
Mash. Add margarine and 1/2 cup cheese. Stir until melted.
Add milk, crackers and eggs.
Season to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven until slightly brown around edges of a buttered casserole dish.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container.
Use 1 to 2 tablespoons per cup of hot water.
Store in tightly covered container.
Variations may be made according to taste for chocolate, sugar and creamer.

title: sunday pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding milk until desired consistency.
I like thin pancakes so I add lots of milk.
This is a Sunday morning favorite.
Serve with butter, maple syrup and bacon.
MMMM-good!

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender; let cool.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Mix soups and tomatoes together; add bell pepper and onion.
In large casserole dish, break chips to cover bottom.
Add chicken in bite size pieces; cover with soup mixture.
Microwave 20 minutes on High; break up more chips in casserole dish and cover chips with cheese.
Microwave 2 or 3 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour into greased casserole dish.

title: dreamy frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and lemon juice, beating until smooth.
Stir in condensed milk, pecans and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and pie filling.
Freeze in 2 (9 x 9 x 2-inch) square dishes or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) dish.
(I prefer to freeze in miniature muffin tins and store in Tupperware container in freezer.)

title: custard pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake until firm and top begins to brown around edges.
Bake at 350°.

title: lime pickle
directions: Mix cucumbers and lime; cover with water and stir.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and wash 3 times.
Let stand in ice water 3 hours.
Drain off water.
Mix vinegar, salt, spices and sugar. Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Bring to a boil; boil slowly until they turn dark green.

title: quick and easy chicken
directions: Mix equal parts of Oven Fry with Italian bread crumbs; coat chicken.
(Cut chicken up in small pieces for a low-fat alternative to chicken nuggets.)
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (15 to 20 minutes for chicken nuggets).
Serve with sweet sour.

title: edible flowers
directions: Use flowers that have not been fertilized or sprayed, homegrown.
Good for wedding cakes. Remove stamens with fingers. Gently dab with meringue, both sides. Sprinkle generously with sugar. Dry 8 hours. Gently shake off sugar; dry on wire rack.

title: diabetic pudding cupcakes
directions: Mix as usual. This makes about 12 cupcakes.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box, replacing part of the water with 3 tablespoons creme de menthe.
Spread fudge icing while cake is slightly warm.
When completely cool, cover icing with Cool Whip mixed with 3 tablespoons creme de menthe.

title: party fig newtons
directions: Slice each Fig Newton into 3 pieces.
Roll in powdered sugar. Adds to your party!

title: cheese cake dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla. Store in refrigerator. Serve with graham crackers, angel food cake cubes and/or fresh fruit.

title: keepsake brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water. Remove from heat. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Stir in walnuts. Mix and sift flour and salt; add gradually, mixing well. Pour into greased and floured 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool thoroughly before cutting into squares.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all together; beat 5 minutes.
Put into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove cake from oven and poke all over top with fork.
Mix 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar with juice of 2 lemons.
Pour mixture over top.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an oblong pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and milk; pour fruit over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: kid's favorite broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and drain.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine rice, broccoli and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Lightly spray an ovenproof casserole dish with vegetable spray.
Spread mixture evenly in dish and cover with cheese.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: chili-cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for eight minutes.
Cool completely before storing in an airtight container.
May be frozen.

title: oatmeal tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into frozen tart shells. Will make 12 to 14 tarts if you fill the tarts half full.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes on a cookie sheet.

title: mexican torta
directions: Place bell peppers and red pepper in food processor work bowl fitted with steel blade or in blender container; cover and process until well blended.
Stir in sour cream and sugar.
Makes about 2 cups sauce.

title: date-nut chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 1 inch apart on prepared cookie sheets.
Bake one sheet at a time 12 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned around edges.
Cool on sheets on wire racks.
Scrape off with spatula.
Store airtight.

title: chicken tandori
directions: Whisk mustard and oil.
Add cumin and coriander.
Add remaining ingredients.
Marinate overnight.
Grill for 20 to 25 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: royal raspberry cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cream margarine with mixer.
Add sugar gradually, beating well after each addition, until light and fluffy.
Stir in egg; beat 1 minute. Combine milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Alternate with milk/vanilla mixture, beating well after each addition.
Spread cake batter in greased, floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the berries evenly over top of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until center of cake springs back when lightly touched. Cool 5 minutes.
Combine vanilla, powdered sugar and cream or milk with melted butter.
Spread over cake; leave berries exposed. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: milnot cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add jello; blend well.
Fold in stiffly whipped Milnot.
(Can be done with electric mixer.)
Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter together.
Put 2/3 of mixture on bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add filling; sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Cut into squares; serve plain or garnished with fruit.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: banana pancakes
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine buttermilk and soda, stirring well.
Add banana, egg substitute and oil.
Stir well.
Add buttermilk mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley with mixer.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with vegetables of choice, chopped real small.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cut in small pieces and serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop and combine pecans, celery and pineapple.
Set aside. Grind cranberries in blender.

title: three vegetable soup(creamed)
directions: Lightly saute onion in butter.
Add broth.
Add zapped vegetables.
Cook for about 1/2 hour, stirring often.
Allow for a boil, about 5 minutes.
Add milk or cream, depending upon creaminess desired.
You may also thicken with frozen mashed potatoes instead of milk/cream.
Serve with a dash of paprika on top of a lemon slice floating on top.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water. Bring to a boil. Add peanuts. Cook until golden. Take off heat. Add butter and soda. Pour into aluminum pie pans. Cool, then remove from pans.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix with cocoa.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, cake coloring, margarine and eggs.
Blend until moistened.
Add soda and vinegar; mix into cake mixture.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 2 round pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese tortilla snacks
directions: Soften cream cheese and Cheez Whiz.
Mix together well. Refrigerate for about 2 hours to thicken slightly.
Spread thin layer of cheese mixture on tortillas.
Roll up tortillas and place in dish.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours or more.
Eat whole or slice into bite size pieces for finger food.

title: bread and butter pickles(light recipe)
directions: Slice and soak cucumbers overnight; drain.
Combine cucumbers and onions.
Bring vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil.
Pour over sliced vegetables and let stand one hour.
Bring all ingredients to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Pack and seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle a little more cheese over the top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or microwave on High for 20 minutes.

title: italian casserole
directions: Cook shells; rinse and drain.
Brown ground beef.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in sauce (onions, black olives or fresh mushrooms are good in sauce).
Simmer 20 minutes.
Use two cake pans.
Line the bottoms with 1/2 the macaroni; cover shells with 1/2 meat sauce.
Spread 1/2 pint sour cream over sauce.
Sprinkle 1/2 of both cheeses.
Repeat 2nd layer.
Cover and bake 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly brown.

title: irresistible peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, shortening, light brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix until blended.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes until just beginning to brown.
Cool for 2 minutes.
Remove cookies.
Place on foil.
Add Hershey's Kisses to center of cookies.
Allow time to cool completely.

title: ken's potato salad
directions: In large bowl, cube cooked potatoes in 1-inch cubes.
Add diced
celery stalks, chopped onion, and chopped hard boiled eggs. Mix in spices, sugar, and vinegar.
Gradually mix in mayo to desired consistency.
Chill for at least three hours. Add salt & pepper to taste before serving.
Garnish with paprika for a perfect summer salad.

title: oriental pork and cabbage
directions: Trim fat from pork tenderloin; cut pork with grain into 2-inch strips.
Cut strips across grain into 1/4-inch slices.
(For ease in cutting, partially freeze pork, about 1 1/2 hours.)
Toss pork with soy sauce, sesame oil, cornstarch, sugar, salt, pepper and garlic in glass or plastic bowl or heavy plastic bag.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix ingredients well (don't put yeast in hot water); add 3 cups flour, 1/2 cup at a time, kneading until smooth.
Let rest 5 to 10 minutes.
Knead well; place in greased bowl and refrigerate. Will last up to 2 weeks.
Take out what you need; place in or on greased pan.
Let rise and bake at 350° until brown.
Make rolls or loaf, which every you need.

title: cheese cake sour cream topping
directions: Mix well and put in spring pan and refrigerate.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all in blender.

title: penne with tomatoes, olives and two cheeses
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons oil in large Dutch oven over medium heat. Add onion and garlic; saute until onion is translucent.
Mix in tomatoes, basil and red pepper.
Bring to boil, breaking tomatoes. Add broth.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat to medium and simmer until mixture thickens to chunky sauce and is reduced to 6 cups, stirring occasionally; cook about 1 1/2 hours.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer half each of first 5 ingredients in a 3-quart glass bowl. Whisk together the rest of ingredients until smooth. Spread half of Parmesan dressing over top. Repeat layers. Cover and chill 8 hours. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: alapilaf(bulgur)
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add vegetables and bulgur.
Stir constantly until vegetables are tender and bulgur is golden.
Add seasonings and bouillon.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in parsley and pimiento just before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tasty cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add all other ingredients except peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Mix well. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
When you take cake out of the oven, spread peanut butter and chocolate chips over warm cake. As they melt, spread evenly. Refrigerate immediately for a few hours or overnight.

title: denny's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, grated cheese and pepper in a large bowl.
Lightly flour cutlets on both sides.
Saute cutlets in oil 2 or 3 minutes on both sides each and remove.
In frying pan saute onion lightly in a little olive oil, then add crushed tomatoes and wine and seasoning.
Simmer 10 minutes.
In roasting pan, put half the tomato mixture on bottom, spreading sauce around, then add the chicken cutlets.
Spread out; top with rest of sauce and then add the Mozzarella cheese to each cutlet.
Cover pan with aluminum foil; bake for 40 minutes.

title: apricot nectar sauce(to put over ham slices)
directions: Combine all the ingredients and cook for around 2 to 3 minutes on the stove until it thickens some. The main thing is to let the brown sugar melt well.
Put in a serving dish and pour over ham slices.

title: oven fries
directions: Slice potatoes into wedges without peeling.
While potatoes are wet, coat with Parmesan and flour.
Melt 1 stick margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place potatoes in one layer in pan and bake at 350°.
Turn after approximately 15 to 20 minutes and continue baking until slightly golden and tender, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crab quiche(microwave)
directions: Spread crab into pie shell.
Add cheese.
Mix eggs, pepper, salt, nutmeg and cream in small bowl; stir thoroughly.
Pour cream mixture over crab.
Dot with pimento.
Cook, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes (turning twice) or until set.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: layered mexican dip(low-fat)
directions: Brown onion in liquid Butter Buds.
Add cooked turkey.
Stir refried beans into turkey mixture.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, sprayed with cooking spray.
Sprinkle green chilies on top of turkey-bean mixture.
Spread 1/2 cheese over, then pour taco sauce over cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and spoon sour cream on top.
Serve with homemade low-fat chips.

title: apple cheese bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese, apples and nuts until well blended.
Stir in cheese, apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Grease 1 loaf bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine chocolate bits, evaporated milk and butter in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until creamy and smooth.
Combine remaining ingredients and gradually stir in the chocolate mixture. Pour into pie shell and bake in moderate oven (375°) for 40 minutes until firm.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients in roaster pan.
Lay fryer around in mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, covered.

title: quick macaroni and beef
directions: Saute beef in butter, if needed.
Drain.
Add onion and cook until wilted.
Add chili powder, salt, pepper, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and cook over medium heat 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large saucepan.
