Bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Simmer gently, partly covered, for 40 minutes or until barley is tender.

title: better-than-almost-anything cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake cake as directed on package for 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
Poke top of warm cake every 1/2-inch with handle of wooden spoon, wiping handle occasionally to reduce sticking.
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk evenly over top of cake.
Let stand until milk has been absorbed into cake. Drizzle with caramel topping.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours or until chilled.
Spread whipped topping over top of cake. Sprinkle with toffee chips.
Cover and refrigerate any remaining cake.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix with pastry blender until crumbles together.
Press part of mixture in a greased 14 x 11-inch pan.
Add 2 cans of fruit pie filling.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top of the fruit.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: yellow squash muffins
directions: Cut squash in 1-inch slices.
Cook 15 or 20 minutes, until tender.
Drain well and mash.
Measure 2 cups.
Combine with eggs and butter; mix.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl. Make a well in center of flour mixture.
Add squash mixture, stirring until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: gorp
directions: Combine all in large bowl except peanut butter, butter and marshmallows.
Melt these over low heat.
Pour over cereal.
Mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Place chicken in large casserole.
Cover with onions and mushrooms.
Layer cream soups over onion and mushrooms.
Pour wine over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for at least 1 hour.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk, pudding and half of Cool Whip until thick.
Layer wafers, pudding and bananas and then top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with crushed wafers. Refrigerate until it sets.

title: over the top nachos
directions: In a large frying pan, brown ground beef with, onion, salt and pepper.
Break the meat up into very small pieces while cooking, then drain.

title: chicken pie
directions: Saute vegetables with oleo.
When tender, add flour, chicken broth and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until it boils. Add chicken and pour into large greased pan.
Make biscuit dumplings and put biscuits around edges of pan.
Brush with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven until biscuits are golden brown, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: marshmallow graham
directions: Combine marshmallows, butter and milk or cream; add crushed graham crackers.
Mix well.
Press into pan; cool.
Toss with whipped cream.
If desired, dates can be added.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill dough.
Bake in muffin pans (greased).
Bake 20 minutes in 425° oven.

title: speedy spinach lasagne
directions: Empty spaghetti sauce mix into saucepan; add tomato paste, tomato sauce and water.
Heat, stirring, until well blended. Remove from heat.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into a casserole bowl.
Add melted cheese; stir until mixed.
Set oven at 350°.
Bake in oven for approximately 25 minutes, or until done.

title: pull-apart bacon cheese wreath(happy holidays)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut a 12-inch square of aluminum foil and press on bottom and sides of 9-inch round cake pan.
Place inverted 3 1/2-inch custard cup in center of pan.
Lightly grease foil and sides of custard cup; set aside.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place rolls (don't separate) in ungreased jelly roll pan (10 x 15 x 1-inch).
Pull rolls up to sides of pan.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes, leaving rolls flat.
Mix dressing with sour cream. Spread party dip over crust.
Arrange vegetables on top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and chopped chives.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and whip until creamy.
Pour in Eagle Brand, vanilla and real lemon.
Whip until creamy and mixed.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill about 3 hours, then top with fruit filling.

title: quick and easy chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix one quart milk and pudding mix; add Dime Brand milk.
Mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer and add remaining milk.
Freeze as usual.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: peg's corn muffins
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add all dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add corn meal.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken rice
directions: Mix in separate bowl everything but rice.
Place rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Layer with chicken, then top with liquid mixture.
Cover with foil.
No peeking! Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: baked ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wipe
ham with damp paper towel. Place ham on rack in
shallow pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours. Place potatoes, onions
and
2 teaspoons salt in large saucepan. Cover with water.
Bring
to
a
boil;
boil
for 5 minutes and drain.

title: spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the sugar and butter.
Add molasses and water to sugar mixture and mix well.
In separate bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to the creamed mixture and stir until smooth.
Drop by tablespoonful onto nonstick cookie sheet.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 60 cookies.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt. Add Crisco and mix well. Add egg, vinegar and water; mix until well blended. Place in covered bowl or wrap in wax paper and place in plastic bag. Store in refrigerator. This will keep for 2 weeks or longer. Yield: 3 to 4 pie shells (9-inch) or 2 two-crust pies.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix well.

title: midwest vegetable crunch
directions: Wash vegetables and cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix in large bowl and toss with dressing.
Marinate for at least 2 hours.

title: party mix
directions: Mix
the last five ingredients on stove until margarine melts. Pour over Krispies, Chex, Cheerios, pretzels and nuts. Bake
in big
dish
pan
for 2 hours at 250°.
Stir and shake every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in closed containers.

title: apple and raisin muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Add to egg mixture; mix well until well blended.
Add raisins.
Spoon batter into well-greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° until done 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: five decker dinner
directions: Cut slices of bacon into one-inch pieces.
Place in bottom of skillet or Dutch oven.
Make ground beef into four patties and place on top of bacon.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Over this, place layers of sliced vegetables, onions, potatoes and carrots. Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Last, layer green pepper on top.
Place skillet or Dutch oven over medium heat and cook for 3 minutes, after bacon begins to sizzle.
Add can of tomato sauce.
Cover and turn heat to low and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.

title: brandied spice coffee
directions: Place coffee in blender or food processor fitted with a steel blade.
With processor running, add brandy extract.
Stop and scrape sides of container with a spatula.
Process 10 seconds longer.
Place mix in a small bowl and add remaining ingredients. Store in refrigerator.
Yields eight 6 ounce servings.

title: stuffed flounder filets
directions: Saute onions in butter until clear. Add parsley, onion tops and bell peppers. Cook until tender (about 2 to 3 minutes). Remove from heat and let cool. Add beaten egg and water. Stir thoroughly and add shrimp and crabmeat and toss gently. Add bread crumbs to make dressing consistency. Spread stuffing on half of each filet and fold over, fastening with toothpicks. Sprinkle paprika over each piece and place in greased baking pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven, basting with margarine, lemon juice and parsley flakes often. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. You can also cover with bread crumbs to make crispier.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Sugar should be melted well.
Add cucumbers and let sit 1 hour.
Put in jars.
Cover with juice and freeze. Very crisp and tasty pickles.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix with fingers.
Roll into small balls.
Cook at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients into a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add 3/4 cup peanut butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Beat until the mixture begins to get thick.
Pour into a buttered dish.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Mix jello.
Let set until starting to get thick.
Mix sweetened strawberries with jello.
Fold Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together.
Pinch up cake.
Put one layer of angel food cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Cover with strawberries and jello, layer of Cool Whip and milk, then a layer of cake and layer of strawberries; Cool Whip.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Let set a few hours in refrigerator.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, egg and molasses.
Add all spices and vanilla.
Alternate with flour and coffee.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Make fork lines; sprinkle lightly with sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, remove 1 cup and set aside.
To remaining mixture add egg, buttermilk and soda.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in mixture and sprinkle with reserved cup of crumbs.
Then sprinkle broken bits of Heath candy bars.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
May frost cake, also.

title: lo-cal punchbowl cake
directions: Put the cake pieces in bottom of pan.
Mix pudding.
Add cherries and pecans to pudding and let set just a few minutes, then pour over cake pieces.
Refrigerate.
Next day, top with light Cool Whip.

title: homemade tartar sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in blender.
Cover and process on "blend" until onion is chopped.
Stir in Salad Delites or Bill Delites.
Yields 3/4 cups.

title: cool carrot-orange soup
directions: Cook onion in oil until transparent.
Add carrots.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Puree in blender until smooth.
Pour mixture into metal bowl; set into bowl of ice.
Add in orange juice; stir until cold.
Stir in yogurt until smooth.
Serves 2.

title: caramel snakes
directions: Heat caramels and water over low heat, stirring frequently, until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large covered casserole.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Uncover the casserole to brown for the last 20 minutes.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: pineapple cottage cheese green salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add milk and mayonnaise.
Blend well.
Add orange juice, pineapple and cottage cheese.
Mix well. Pour into mold.
Let stand overnight or until set.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Grease a loaf pan (use butter or oleo).
Combine sugar, milk, corn
syrup
and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat,
stirring
constantly
until sugar is dissolved. Cook, stirring occasionally, to 234° on candy thermometer (or until small
amount
of
mixture dropped into very cold water forms
a soft
balls which flatters when removed from water). Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and butter.
Cool mixture to
120°, without
stirring.	Bottom of pan will be lukewarm. Add
vanilla and
beat
vigorously
for	5 to 10 minutes with wooden
spoon until
candy
is
thick
and
no longer glossy. Spread in prepared pan.
Cool until firm and cut into squares.

title: barbecued armadillo
directions: Remove the shell and skin and wash thoroughly.
Soak the armadillo in salty water overnight in the refrigerator.
Cut the armadillo into pieces like chicken.
Place in covered pot and cover with water and add crab boil.
Boil for 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove and brown in butter, then place in shallow baking dish and brush on mixture of melted butter, Dale's steak seasoning, liquid smoke and barbecue sauce.
Bake at 300° for one hour.
Baste every 20 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: no ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into small balls. Place into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour the following sauce over balls and bake 15 minutes more.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
When wanted, fill greased muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until macaroni is tender.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown onion and pepper in margarine.
Add other ingredients, mix and pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sauerkraut (cut with kitchen shears if stringy) with celery, pimento, onion, pepper and large carrot.
Mix in another bowl 2/3 cup vinegar with salad oil, sugar and celery seed (dressing).
Combine dressing and pour over vegetables.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Keeps a long time in the refrigerator.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add tomatoes and seasonings.
Mix beaten eggs with cottage cheese (Ricotta cheese may be substituted for cottage cheese).
Layer sauce, noodles, sauce, eggs, noodles, sauce and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let rest before cutting.

title: stew
directions: Cut roast into bite size chunks and let simmer, slow, until tender (use as little water as possible for a more beefy taste). Add your potatoes (cut as you wish) and can of corn.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon slightly.
Add all ingredients to beans.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir several times.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Combine
graham cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Use the mixture to line a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: crabmeat bisque
directions: Mix and
heat:	Milk,
soup and Old Bay seasoning.
Add crabmeat.
Cut off heat and add (while hot) cream cheese.
Add sherry at time of serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter rectangular pan; pour pineapple and juice in pan.
Pour cherry pie filling on pineapple.
Sprinkle entire cake mix over cherries (dry cake mix).
Pat 2 sticks butter over dry cake mix. Sprinkle coconut over mix and pecans over coconut. Bake at 350° for one hour.
Almost any kind of pie filling can be used.

title: chasen's famous chili(esquire 1973)
directions: Wash beans; add water 2-inches above and soak overnight. Simmer, covered, in same water until tender.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Saute green peppers slowly in oil for 5 minutes. Add onions and cook until tender, stirring frequently. Add garlic and parsley.
In large skillet, melt butter and saute beef for 15 minutes.
Stir in chili powder and cook for 10 minutes; add this mixture to beans and season with salt, pepper and cumin.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Remove cover and cook for 30 minutes longer.
Skim off fat.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: zesty shrimp dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese and fold in all other ingredients except shrimp.
Drain shrimp and add liquid to cream cheese mixture until it reaches a dip consistency.
Fold in shrimp. Serve with sturdy chips, such as Doritos.

title: classic 7-up pound cake
directions: Combine butter, shortening, sugar and extracts in a large bowl. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: mints
directions: Mix all with mixer. Roll in small balls. Roll in sugar.
Press in rubber mint mold or roll into log shape. Chill and slice thin. Dip into sugar.
May also be coated.
Do not dip in sugar if coating with melted chocolate.

title: strawberry angel salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on package.
Chip bananas and strawberries into jello.
Add sugar and divide into 2 parts.
Pour 1 part in dish and place in refrigerator until set.
When set, spread sour cream over jello.
Pour second part of jello mixture over sour cream and return to refrigerator.

title: coconut delight candy
directions: Mix margarine, milk and sugar together.
Let come to a boil and stir constantly for 2 1/2 minutes rapidly.
Take off heat and add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Add crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
No further cooking necessary.

title: mexican rice
directions: Saute the rice in hot oil until golden brown.
Add onion, garlic and vegetables.
Cook slightly.
Add boiling stock, salt and tomato sauce.
Return to a boil, then lower heat, cover and cook on low heat for about 25 minutes or until rice is tender and the liquid has absorbed.

title: robyn's wedding punch
directions: Mix frozen lemonade per directions on the can.
Add pineapple juice and lemon-lime soda.
Drop spoonfuls of sherbet into mixture.
Make 1 punch bowl size.
You can change the flavor by using different juice and sherbet.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: In blender, put ingredients in order given.
Blend for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased pie plates.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: dinner-in-a-dish
directions: Put shortening in skillet and lightly fry peppers and onions for 3 minutes.
Then add meat and blend thoroughly.
Add seasonings.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs and mix well.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar until creamy. Blend in 2 cups of thawed Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill at least three hours.

title: new magic spice cake
directions: Sift together the first 7 ingredients.
Add brown sugar, shortening and buttermilk.
Beat 2 minutes and add 2/3 to 3/4 cup eggs or 3 medium eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheesy pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops lightly with salt and pepper.
Place in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top each chop with an onion slice (optional).
Spread each slice with 1 teaspoon mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix onions, 1 pkg. beef, worcestershire sauce, Accent and cream cheese.
Mix with hands and shape into ball.
Dice 1 pkg. beef into small pieces.
Cover ball with diced beef.
Set in fridge overnight.

title: chicken sibelius
directions: Season chicken with salt and poultry seasoning.
Melt margarine in large skillet; add chicken and saute until brown. Arrange asparagus in bottom of a greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup, cream and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and asparagus.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit salad dessert
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sour cream together. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream lard and brown sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: easy lemonade
directions: Measure amount of Country Time lemonade mix to make 2 quarts. Add sugar and lemon juice and mix well.
Add enough water to fill container to 2 quarts.
Chill before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: Heat butter in 3-quart saucepan and saute onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add carrots, celery, potatoes, parsley, chicken broth, dill weed, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Add pimento and 3 1/2 cups milk.
Heat soup until milk is scalded only; do not boil.
Blend flour with cold milk and add it to the soup, stirring constantly.
Cook until soup starts to simmer and is slightly thickened.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: pinch cake
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Shake biscuits into sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Layer in a tube or Bundt pan.
After each layer, spread chopped nuts.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Place on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cooked chicken.
Mix soup, one-half of the cheese and onion.
Add milk, mayonnaise and eggs.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Top with bread crumbs and rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham casserole
directions: Put ham and cheese through food chopper.
Cook pasta in salt water.
Mix al ingredients, except bread crumbs and pour into baking dish.
Cover and place in oven for about 35 minutes. Remove; add bread crumbs and brown.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Saute
garlic
in
oil	until brown; then discard.
Add tomatoes,
salt, pepper and basil.	Simmer until well blended. (Medium
heat,
about 12 minutes.) Cook until all the water is gone.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet.
Add onions and cook until light brown.
Add shrimp (cut in half if large).
Add salt and pepper to eggs.
Add mushrooms.
Scramble together.
Add cold rice and cook until rice is coated with egg and hot.

title: pecan cheese pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients and pour in pie crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Mix eggs in large bowl (blender) at medium speed until frothy.
Add corn syrup, 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well and pour over pecans.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes on center rack.
Place on wire rack to cool.
Serves 10.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add meat until cooked.
Add other ingredients.
Serve over noodles.
(You can substitute with ground beef.)

title: minted cucumbers in sour cream(really good and so refreshing)
directions: Pare cucumbers thinly.
Slice 1/8-inch thick into mixing bowl. Sift 1 1/2 teaspoons of the salt over cucumbers and toss gently to distribute.
Cover and refrigerate 20 to 30 minutes.

title: "western style chili"
directions: Brown hamburger and drain after cooking.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix hamburger, onions and macaroni.
Stir in chili hot beans and tomato sauce.
Add chili powder, a little at a time. Stir until it's well mixed.

title: marinade for brisket
directions: Mix well.
Use like salt.
Marinate 24 hours.
Put on smoker for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Make pastry; roll half very thin and use to line a 2-inch deep baking pan.
Roll other half and cut into 2-inch strips.
Bake half the strips in a preheated 375° oven until lightly browned.
Put berries, 1 cup sugar and water into a saucepan.
Cook until berries are soft.
Mix flour and 1/4 cup sugar; add to berries.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture has thickened slightly.
Spoon berries into pastry lined pan with cooked pastry strips stirred through filling.
Dot with butter.
Cover with remainder of pastry strips (uncooked).
Bake at 425° until pastry is brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugars and shortening. Sift flour, soda and salt. Combine shortening mixture, flour mixture, water and vanilla. Roll in small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Crisscross with fork. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook fryer until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and debone it.
Reserve broth for dumplings.
Mix flour with salt and cooking oil.
Add enough water to form a ball.
Place on floured surface and knead until just stiff enough to handle easily when rolled thin.
Sprinkle with black pepper and roll once more.
Cut into strips.
Drop dumplings one at a time into gently boiling broth and cook until tender.

title: vidalia onion and steak salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
In a small bowl, combine London Broil, radishes and onion.
Pour dressing on top.
Toss well.

title: crackling bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake in 450° oven until done.

title: chocolate bonbons(unbaked)
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt; add milk and butter.
Blend in beaten egg yolks.
Cook in top of double boiler (water in bottom) 20 minutes.
Don't be disturbed if mixture looks peculiar.
Stir constantly until thick.
Remove from fire; add vanilla, chocolate bits and nuts.
Cool; chill in refrigerator.
Roll in small balls and roll in moist coconut or ground walnuts.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Soak dried beef a few minutes to get out some of the salt. Drain.
Let cheese soften; finely chop beef and olives.
Add onion soup, Worcestershire sauce and 3/4 of the beef to soft cheese. Roll into ball.
Roll the ball in the remaining chopped beef. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: cheeseburger 'n' fries casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown the beef; drain.
Stir in soups.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Arrange French fries on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 50-55 minutes or until the fries are golden brown.

title: cream puff ring
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour and salt. Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Drop ten 1/2 cupfuls of dough on lightly greased cookie sheet to form 9-inch ring.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Cool.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13 baking dish, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients, press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool; chill if desired. Cut into bars at room temperature.

title: broken-glass cake
directions: Prepare orange, cherry and lime gelatins separately, using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour each flavor into 8-inch square pan and chill until firm.

title: easy hollandaise sauce
directions: Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until butter melts and sauce is slightly thick.
Season to taste with salt.
Makes 1/2 cup sauce.

title: ham rolls
directions: Allow cream cheese to set until room temperature.
Cut roots off onions and clean thoroughly.
Spread cheese on ham slices and place whole onion on top of cheese.
Cut off extra green part of onion, roll and place in freezer until cold (5 to 10 minutes). Then slice into bite size pieces.
Place on platter and serve. Great for parties.

title: honey-glazed acorn squash
directions: Halve squash and remove seeds and discard stringy fibers.
Put cut side down in shallow baking pan and add 1/2 hot water.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove squash and pour off water.
Turn squash cut side up.
Mix remaining ingredients and divide among squash.
Bake, basting twice with glaze about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve with fresh strawberries, pineapple, honeydew, cantaloupe or any fruit.

title: black walnut icing
directions: Heat milk and let cool.
Combine with other ingredients and cook until thick, stirring constantly.

title: cherry cheese charmer
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Add lemon and cherry juice.
Pour 1 1/2 cups of jello mixture into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex and chill until firm.
Mash cream cheese; add small amount of remaining jello and blend.
Chill remaining jello mixture until slightly thickened.
Whip, then add cream cheese mixture, gradually blending with beater.
Add cherries.
Pour over firm jello and chill.

title: little pizzas
directions: Brown sausage and lean chuck.
Drain most of grease off.
Add spices and cheese.
When cheese is melted, spread on bread and put on a cookie sheet in freezer until firm.
After frozen, stack in plastic bags and store in freezer.
Take out as many as you need and put under broiler for about 5 minutes.
Very good to serve as a pick-up.

title: quick 'n easy sausage casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, mushrooms, celery, condensed soup and 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Arrange Brown 'N Serve sausage atop casserole. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Melt butter in baking pan or dish.
Place chicken filets, one layer thick, in pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Put Ragu sauce over chicken. Add Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Add Mozzarella cheese and bake 15 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: tamale pie
directions: Fry onion and garlic in bacon fat until brown.
Add beef and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until brown.
Add tomato sauce, corn, olives and seasonings and simmer on low heat. Meantime, prepare muffin mix.
Place meat mixture in shallow casserole (well-greased).
Cover with muffin mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Cook in double boiler for 7 minutes. Beat with mixer while cooking.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and chop; set aside. Mix sugar and eggs until creamy. Sift together the flour, soda, salt and baking powder. Mix dry ingredients, oil and vanilla into egg mixture. Add apples. Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt the butter or margarine over low heat.
Blend in 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Heat until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Add gradually, stirring in 1 cup milk.
Cook rapidly, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens. Cook 2 minutes longer.
Makes 1 cup.

title: lemon chicken almondine
directions: Place chicken in a large shallow baking dish.
Combine lemon juice, mustard, garlic and pepper in a small bowl.
Beat in oil. Pour over chicken. Marinate 1 hour at room temperature.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in 1/2 cup candies.

title: sweet potato and pecan pancakes
directions: Combine flour, 2 tablespoons pecans, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice and salt in a large bowl. Combine milk, brown sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs; add to the flour mixture, stirring until smooth. Stir in sweet potatoes. Spoon 1/4 cup batter onto a hot griddle. Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles.
Serve pancakes hot with 1 teaspoon pecans sprinkled on top. Yield: 12 pancakes.

title: meat loaf in tomato sauce with macaroni
directions: In large bowl, mix meat loaf ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Shape in 15 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch loaf.
In Dutch oven with nonstick finish or coating, heat oil.
Add meat loaf and brown.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients except macaroni; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.

title: french green beans
directions: Cook beans according to directions.
Slice water chestnuts; throw liquid away.
Grease casserole with butter.
Place a layer of beans, a layer of soup and a layer of water chestnuts.
Repeat. Cover and cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Take lid off.
Place can of French-fried onion rings on top and heat again.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook as regular pancakes. These are very tender, different but good.

title: grandma's depression rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add salt and sugar. Add 3 cups warm water and flour alternately to yeast mixture, beating well.
When all flour and water are added, dough will be sticky.
Allow to rise for 2 hours.
Turn mixture onto a floured board and knead for a few minutes.
Add flour to board as you need to make dough smooth.

title: clone of a cinnabon
directions: Place ingredients in the pan of the bread machine in the order recommended by the manufacturer.
Select dough cycle; press Start.

title: viva's fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; add other ingredients in order.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Boil the milk, sugar, 1/2 cup margarine and chocolate chips on low heat.
After it has come to a boil, start timing for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool syrup completely. Crush Oreos and mix with 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Lightly press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer vanilla ice cream on Oreos.
Pour syrup on top (after it is completely cooled).
Freeze.

title: spicy black bean chili
directions: Place chicken in a medium skillet with 3/4 cup of water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 12 to 14 minutes or until no longer pink.
Drain and cool.
Use a fork to pull chicken apart into long, thin shreds; set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan, cook onion, bell pepper and garlic in hot oil over medium-high heat until tender, but not brown.
Stir in chili powder, oregano and cilantro; cook for 1 minute more.
Drain stewed tomatoes, reserving juices.
Set aside.
Add reserved tomato juice, beer and lime juice to onion mixture; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Coarsely chop the stewed tomatoes; add tomatoes, shredded chicken, black beans, jalapenos and crushed red pepper to onion mixture.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes more or until most of the liquid is absorbed (should be thick).
Garnish with cilantro sprigs and serve with warm tortillas or cornbread. Serves 4.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Add cold water to liquid to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened. Stir in Cool Whip with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut. Spoon into a 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm. Unmold on bed of lettuce.
Makes 10 servings.

title: toasted oat muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. In large bowl, combine flour, toasted oats, nuts, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl, combine buttermilk, oil, honey and egg; mix well.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon about 1/4 cup batter into each greased or lined muffin cup.
(Muffin cups will be very full.) Bake at 400° for 12 to 16 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: the bloody mary
directions: Mix and pour over ice and vodka.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Add soup to boiling water.
Add all ingredients together. Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serves 12.
This is a hearty main meal.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of an 8-inch pan. Set aside.
In medium size bowl add cream cheese and next 7 ingredients and mix until smooth.
Add egg whites and mix until blended.
Fold in chocolate morsels.
Slowly pour mixture over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cheesecake is set.
Let cool in pan on wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Transfer cheesecake to serving platter.
Serves 12.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Wash well and dry 1 cup up fryer chicken.
Arrange pieces, skin side up in a shallow baking dish.
Pour over melted butter. Combine mustard, vinegar, paprika, salt, pepper and minced onions. Mix well.
Spread over chicken.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: crunchy ham casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in casserole.
Top with potato chips and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: crab salad rolls
directions: Combine crabmeat with celery, cucumbers, green onions and mayonnaise.
Chill until ready to serve.
Toast open-faced rolls under toaster oven or broiler until brown.
Spoon crabmeat into rolls.
Serve while rolls are still warm.
(Rolls may be cut in half to make small sandwiches.)

title: banana date bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In a separate bowl, beat at medium speed the eggs, syrup and corn oil.
Add bananas.
Stir in flour mixture until moist.
Stir in dates and walnuts.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: western baked beans
directions: Pan-fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on towel; set aside.
Place onion rings in large skillet and add the sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Add onion mixture to the beans.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake covered 1/2 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer. Crumble bacon over beans.
Makes 12 servings.

title: batter pie
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch baking dish generously with butter.
Pour batter in dish.
Add fruit to top of batter.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from crushed pineapple and heat juice to boiling point.
Pour over jello and dissolve.
Beat cream cheese, then add jello mixture.
Add small bottle of Coke.
When mixture begins to jell, add pineapple and nuts.

title: shrimp and pineapple salad
directions: Probably the most famous of all composed salads is this one of tuna and vegetables.
It is a perfect luncheon dish, or it may be served in small portions as a first course.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add cocoa; stir until smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk; cook and stir constantly until mixture is thick, smooth and glossy, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Cover; refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or until firm.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls; roll in cocoa or powdered sugar.
Refrigerate until firm 1 to 2 hours. Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: angel fluff
directions: Mix all together and put into the freezer.
Let thaw 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You may add celery, onions, olives, and peppers to your taste.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: kraut slaw
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Let set for 4 to 6 hours or until cold.

title: avocado spread
directions: In medium bowl, mash avocado with fork.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and chill for 1 hour.
Serve on toasted bread, crackers or chips.
Serves 8.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and form a ball.
Chill. When ready to serve, cover with cocktail sauce and serve with crackers.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add liquid when ready to fry.
(You may need to add a little water to batter.)
Drop by teaspoon into hot grease.

title: chocolate creme dessert
directions: Blend together; then press into a large baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake 15 minutes at 350°; then let cool for about 10 or 15 minutes.
Do not let crust brown!

title: casserole roma
directions: Grease a 3-quart casserole dish or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Layer potatoes, corn, onion, beef and carrots. Season each layer with salt. Pour spaghetti sauce over all. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 3/4 hours. Serves 6.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion until tender.
Combine mushroom soup (golden) and sour cream.
Stir in carrots and add zucchini and onion.
With fork, mix melted butter and stuffing.
Spread 2/3 of stuffing in 7 x 11-inch pan lightly greased.
Spoon mixture over the top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture over all.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fat-free oatmeal honey raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl combine dry ingredients.
Stir in egg whites, honey and vanilla until well mixed.
Add raisins (batter will be stiff).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets. Bake until almost firm, do not overbake.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: easy egg custard
directions: Mix together all 5 ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix hamburg.
Make small meat balls.
Cook sauce ingredients 1/2 hour, stirring often.
Add meat balls and simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve as an appetizer or as a main dish over rice or noodles.

title: light peach salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed.
You can cut water just slightly.
Stir in 9 to 12 ounce Cool Whip.
Then add fresh chopped peaches or drained sliced peaches that have been chopped.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together soft shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift together soda, sifted flour, salt and cream of tartar and stir in.
Chill dough.

title: potatoes with cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake covered for 1 hour at 300°. Uncover and bake 20 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool.
Slice in half lengthwise and scoop out potato, leaving 1/4 in skin.
Put potato in bowl; add Mozzarella cheese, milk and butter.
Mix as for mashed potatoes.
Refill potato skins; decorate with any of the following:
chopped green or red pepper, chopped chives, shredded Cheddar cheese, chopped bacon, paprika, spices as desired.
Before serving, bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: old fashion gingerbread
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt. Cream together shortening and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Use mixer at medium speed and beat in egg and molasses. Add dry ingredients, a little at a time, with hot water.
Beat well, using mixer set on low speed.
Pour batter into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Make sure you use only a 9-inch square pan or gingerbread will by dry.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in a large bowl; set aside. Mix together the pumpkin, corn oil and water.
Add eggs; mix well. Add to dry ingredients; stir until moistened.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until pick comes out clean.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Use 2/3 cup honey for each cup sugar.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add flour and beat.
Add milk and stir well.
Add beaten egg whites.
Stir to mix and bake at 350°.
Bake until golden brown.

title: coolrise white bread
directions: Combine 2 cups of the flour, the undissolved yeast, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Stir to blend.
Add margarine and hot tap water.
Beat with an electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes. Scrape bowl occasionally.
Add 1 more cup flour and beat at high speed for 1 minute or until thick and elastic.
Gradually stir in enough of remaining flour with wooden spoon to make a soft dough which leaves the sides of the bowl.
Turn out onto a floured board.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Cover with a plastic wrap, then a towel (on the kneading board).
Let rest 20 minutes, then punch down; make into loaves and place in two greased bread pans.
Brush tops lightly with oil.
Let raise. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
May cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate up to 24 hours before baking, also.

title: strawberry pretzel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed pretzels, 1/3 cup sugar, and margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Blend until crumbly.
Pat into an 8 x 12-inch pan and bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: money bread
directions: Boil exactly 2 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture over your biscuits in cake pan.
Cut 2 cans of biscuits and shake in mixture as before and arrange in cake pan.
Pour remaining syrup over this and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Brown rice in margarine.
Spread browned rice in a large flat casserole.
Lay pieces of chicken on top of rice.
Overall pour soup, mushrooms, water and sherry (mix in a bowl first, then pour over).
Over the top sprinkle onion soup mix.
Cover completely with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours and do not peek.

title: cedric
directions: Cook, drain and blot meat.
Return to pan.
Add cabbage, tomatoes, tomato sauce and grated cheese to cover mixture.
Simmer on stove, covered, for 45 to 60 minutes.
Add more grated cheese, if desired.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Serve with Wheat Thins, Fritos or crackers.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: apple pudding
directions: Combine apples, 6 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Place in pan and cook until apples are soft.
Place in top of double boiler the beaten eggs, sour cream and sugar. Cook to a custard.
Remove from fire and add vanilla and nutmeg.
Combine custard and apples. Butter bottom and sides of frying pan.
Press graham cracker crumbs on sides and bottom. Pour mixture into pan and sprinkle additional crumbs on top. Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven. (It takes about 2 cups of graham cracker crumbs.)

title: brandy slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Cool.
Boil 2 cups water and steam tea bags for 20 minutes.
Mix all together and put in freezer.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: creamy green bean casserole
directions: In large casserole dish, layer green beans
and onions alternately.
Mix together soup, milk and basil.
Pour over beans and onions.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces and arrange on top of cheese.
Bake in 375° oven about 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Do not drain beans.
Bake uncovered for 40 minutes.

title: cheese ravioli with broccoli pesto
directions: In food processor or blender, combine half of broccoli, oil, cheese, garlic, lemon juice, salt and pepper and whirl until smooth.
Cook ravioli in large pot of boiling water.
Add salt. Cook until done.
Add remaining chopped broccoli to pot.
Cook until heated through, about 1 minute.
Drain ravioli and broccoli and return to warm pot.
Stir broccoli sauce in until well coated. Serve with extra cheese along the side.

title: red beans and rice(bayou country style)
directions: Wash beans.
Soak overnight and drain.
Combine all ingredients in slow cooker; add 3 cups water.
Cook all day on high; add water if needed.
Remove cover 2 hours before serving to thicken.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: cream cheese and beef spread
directions: Soften cream cheese. Chop bell pepper & dried beef fine. Combine all the ingredients, except for the nuts. Form into ball and roll into chopped nuts. Serve with wheat thins.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish (spray with cooking spray first).
Sprinkle generous amount of shredded Mozzarella cheese over top of chicken.
Mix mushroom soup and wine and pour over the chicken.
Mix the melted margarine and crushed croutons and spread over top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°, uncovered, or until chicken is tender.

title: hot cranberry sizzle
directions: Simmer combined ingredients in a saucepan until bubbling. Remove orange peel.
Pour into large mugs.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar. Set aside. Melt butter in 2-quart baking dish. Blend 1 cup sugar with remaining ingredients. Pour over melted butter. Do not stir. Put peaches on top. Bake at 350 for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown. Makes its own crust.

title: sourdough starter
directions: In a large bowl (not aluminum), dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water. Add sugar.
Beat
in
cups
warm
water, flour and salt with beater, mixer or whisk to make smooth batter.
Cover with damp cloth and put in warm place
for
to
days or until foamy and light.
Stir several times a day.
Starter
is
now ready
to
use
or may now be stored in refrigerator in
a
glass jar with lid.
Feed regularly.
A wide mouth jar works well and I feed every time I use some, which is approximately 2 times a week.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers, until the salt is dissolved.
Pour mixture over crackers and mix thoroughly.

title: party meat balls
directions: Blend meat with cornflakes and milk.
Add onion, chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly.
With wet hands, shape meat mixture into 36 small balls, using about 1 teaspoon for each.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Cook until almost tender, about 5 minutes; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate any remaining pie. Serves 6.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased 3-quart casserole. Cover top with bread crumbs and pour another stick of melted margarine on top.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Serves about 30 people.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Cream together 2 sticks margarine, 2 tablespoons vanilla, 2 cups sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time on high speed, then add 1 pint sour cream.
On low speed gradually add 3 cups flour and 2 teaspoons baking soda.
Pour this batter into 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, greased and floured.
Now mix together in small bowl 4 tablespoons margarine, 1 cup brown sugar, 2 tablespoons cinnamon and 6 tablespoons chopped nuts.
Moist and delicious!!

title: creamless cream pie
directions: Stir sugar and flour together.
Scald milk and slowly add to mixture.
Let cool and add vanilla and melted margarine.
Pour into pie crust.
Add meringue and bake until brown.

title: pistachio fruit dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Chill.
Serve with sliced apples, bananas and grapes.
For variation, substitute cherry or strawberry jello for the pudding.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cut margarine into sugar, flour, and salt with pastry blender or fork.
Smooth into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cottage cheese in bowl.
Add undrained pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix Gently.
Fold in whipping cream topping.
Chill.

title: chicken stew 'n dumplings
directions: Sprinkle chicken with 1/2 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper. Brown in butter in large, heavy pan.
Add water, onion and poultry seasoning, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in soup and vegetables, bring to boil, cover and simmer 10 more minutes.
Stir now and then.
Combine biscuit mix and milk; spoon dumplings onto stew.
Cook uncovered 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
This is a nutritious and stupendous meal in one.

title: potatoes and pork(servings:  8)
directions: Peel the potatoes and cut them into two or three pieces.
Cut the pork into 2-inch pieces.
Simmer the potatoes with water (1/2 cup), in a pan on low heat.
After simmering until the potatoes are almost cooked, put the pork on the potatoes.
After a few minutes, season them with Japanese rice-wine, sugar and soy sauce until it is mixed well.

title: honey of a carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) baking pans; set aside.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, add oil, buttermilk, sugar, honey and vanilla. Mix well.
Add flour mixture, pineapple, carrots, coconut, add walnuts.
Stir well.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes, then remove from pans.

title: speedy vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add bay leaf and water.
Heat until boiling. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and cook 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Also great for using any leftover vegetables.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
This recipe can also be used for beef, ham or tuna; just substitute either of these for chicken.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Thaw and drain frozen broccoli.
Mix all ingredients well before adding muffin mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Melt oleo.
Add onions, peppers, garlic, chilies, ginger, salt, sage and cumin.
Add chicken; saute until done and set aside.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Saute chicken breasts on all sides in oil.
Add Basic Spaghetti Sauce.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove chicken from sauce.
Add wine to sauce and simmer for 10 minutes longer, uncovered.
Serve sauce over spaghetti; top with chicken and cheese.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: pink lady
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Bring to a boil crushed pineapple and sugar.
Stir cheese into jello; add pineapple and sugar mixture and stir.
Let jello mixture set halfway; fold in cream and nuts and let set.

title: texas salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and allow to marinate 1 hour before serving.

title: ruston peach crumb pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.

title: spiced oatmeal raisin cookie mix
directions: Layer ingredients into jar in order given.
Press each layer firmly before adding the next ingredient.

title: chocolate surprises
directions: Melt the chips and the margarine in the microwave on Medium (7) in a large (2-quart) glass bowl.
Add the milk and mix.
Add the flour and mix completely.
It will be like play dough. Sometimes it will be a little sticky, but you can still work with it.
With one tablespoon of "dough"
cover a hug completely. Place on nonstick cookie " sheet (or grease a regular one).
Bake at 350° for only 6 minutes.
They will not look done.
Let cool a minute and remove to a wire rack to cool.

title: vegetable bake
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine vegetables, soup and milk along with half of onion rings. Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining onion rings before serving.

title: onion salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions and heat until sugar is dissolved. Pour over onions and refrigerate in a covered container. Serve onion slices and some liquid on lettuce leaves. Will keep for several days. Good with other salads or to put on hamburgers.

title: mama's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add nuts and apples.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to apple mixture.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into Bundt pan, greased and floured.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: ellen's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop finely; transfer to medium bowl.
Stir in cheese and onions.
Add remaining ingredients except paprika and blend well.
Fill caps with mixture, mounding slightly in center.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Arrange in shallow baking dish; microwave on High until heated through, about 4 or 5 minutes.

title: onion bread
directions: Mix together first five ingredients and fill French bread. Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sour cream and sugar together.
Add eggs, 2 at a time; beat well.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla. Pour into 2 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Easy and good.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Roll graham crackers real fine.
Add condensed sweet milk. Add vanilla and chocolate chips.
Mix batter.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 275° for 55 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: *White sauce recipe can be found on the Argo cornstarch box or from any basic cookbook.

title: sue's potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water and some salt.
Boil until tender. Do not overcook.
Drain off water.
Melt margarine in a large pot. Add flour.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Do not let the flour brown. Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Add onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Let sauce thicken, stirring constantly so that it will not scorch.
Add drained potatoes to sauce and allow to simmer for awhile.
You can add some more milk if needed.
Cover with oyster crackers or grated Cheddar cheese before serving.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Mix baking soda in hot water; set aside.
Crem butter and sugar together; add beaten eggs.
Mix completely; set aside.
Cut gumdrops into 2 cups of flour.
Add applesauce to flour; mix well. Add raisins; mix well.
Add walnuts and mix well.
Add butter mixture; mix well.
Add flour with gumdrops; mix well.
Add soda and water; mix well.
Bake in a well-greased and floured angel food cake pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 2 hours.
Cool in pan. Run knife around the sides to loosen.
Remove carefully from pan.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain corn, peas and beans.
Then mix green pepper, celery and pimentos with corn, peas, and beans.
Bring to a boil the oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix well. Chill and Serve.
Keeps for weeks.

title: lorraine's ice cream
directions: Do beat eggs in a heavy large pan.
After well beaten, gradually add sugar while continuing to beat.
Beat until light (a while).
Add 6 cups of milk.
Cook until boils.
Add cream after you pour mixture into ice cream mixer.
Add vanilla and salt.
Let cool by standing in cool water.
Freeze.

title: macaroni ham bake
directions: Put cooked macaroni in buttered baking dish.
Mix soup, milk, onion, 1/2 grated cheese and 1/2 diced ham.
Pour over macaroni and top with remaining cheese and ham.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pan coat
directions: Mix until smooth and keep at room temperature.
Use for any pan that would usually require greasing and flouring.

title: gourmet mayonnaise
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and beat thoroughly. Fold in sour cream.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon half and half and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup half and half into mixing bowl. Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended.
Let stand 3 minutes. Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Mix well. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Garnish with additional whipped topping and nuts as desired.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Cook and stir ground beef in Dutch oven until brown; drain. Add onions, cabbage and celery; cook and stir until vegetables are light brown.
Stir in tomatoes, kidney beans (with liquid), water, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Prepare dumplings and drop by spoonfuls onto boiling stew.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat, 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 more minutes.
Sprinkle dumplings with paprika, if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grind in blender the Cheddar cheese and olives.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Mold in a ball and roll in chopped pecans. May add a cherry to top and parsley leaves for decoration.

title: meatloaf
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Shape into loaf.
Top with catsup.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour in foil-lined pan.

title: cheese and chive biscuits
directions: Combine
first
ingredients
in a large bowl. With a pastry blender,
cut
in
margarine
until
mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in cottage cheese and egg whites just until dry ingredients
are
moistened.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour evenly over work surface. Turn dough out onto floured surface and
knead lightly
to
times.
Roll
dough to 7/8-inch thickness. With a 2-inch biscuit cutter, cut rounds and place on
a
baking sheet sprinkled with cornmeal.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: cranberry sauce salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, add sugar, orange, heated pineapple and juice.
Mash cranberry sauce and add to gelatin mixture.
Add nuts.
Chill in mold until set.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and reserve liquid in saucepan. Flake salmon and mix with other ingredients. Spray loaf pan with non-stick spray. Put mixture in loaf pan and pack tightly. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into muffin lined pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy shrimp bisque
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook mushrooms, green onions and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add broth and shrimp.
Heat to boiling.
Meanwhile, in a cup, stir together flour and cream until well blended.
Stir into broth mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring often.
Add wine and parsley; heat through.
Makes 4 cups or 4 servings.

title: salmon log
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Flake salmon.
Combine salmon, onion, horseradish, cream cheese, lemon juice and salt in bowl; mix well. Shape into log.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 6 servings.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta noodles.
Add olive oil.
Then parboil asparagus for 3 minutes.
Mix in with noodles.
Add other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: dirt
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix together milk, French vanilla pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine together the 2 mixtures.

title: spiced red cabbage
directions: Dice bacon into very small pieces and brown in large, heavy pot until golden.
Add chopped onion and simmer, uncovered.
Add cabbage, garlic, caraway seed and 1/2 cup warm water.
Cover and cook until cabbage starts to soften.
Add salt, pepper, diced pears, lemon halves, red wine and red wine vinegar.
Cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add honey and cook over lowest possible heat, at least 30 minutes.
Cook longer if too
much liquid is present, allowing it to steam away with lid off.
Taste cabbage.
If not sweet enough, add some brown sugar to your liking.
Remove lemon halves.
Cover and cook until cabbage is done.
It should be about 1/3 of its original bulk.
Adjust seasonings and remove from heat.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Combine and serve with rye bread.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add flour and milk.
Cook until thick.
Add Worcestershire sauce and mushroom soup; mix.
Chop pimentos and add pimentos and cheese to sauce.
Mix well.
Put drained green beans in baking dish and pour the sauce over it.
Top with a can of onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fluffy citrus dressing
directions: In saucepan, beat egg.
Add sugar, fruit peels and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick (about 5 minutes). Cool thoroughly.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Makes 2 1/3 cups.

title: cornish pasties
directions: Mince cold meat or thinly slice steak.
Mix all ingredients for filling and divide into 6 or 8 parts.
Divide pastry into 6 or 8 parts.
Roll pastry pieces to the size of a large saucer and place mixture in center of each round.
Wet edges of the pastry half way round, join edges over the top.
Glaze.
Place on a greased sheet.
Bake in a hot oven for first 10 minutes, then reduce the heat.
Cook for another 20 minutes if raw meat is used, 10 minutes for cooked meat.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Bring the sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat; add the peanut butter.
Blend in cornflakes and mix well.
After all is mixed, drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: crunchy seafood casserole
directions: Empty soup and evaporated milk into 2-quart casserole dish. Add tuna, shrimp, onion, celery and nuts.
Mix well.
Season to taste, going light on the salt.
Add 3/4 can chow mein noodles and mix again.
Cover with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda, and salt.
Add together and mix well.
Add pumpkin.
Beat well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: squash bread appetizer
directions: Mix together the oil and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add squash and onion.
Toss to coat.
Arrange in an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour oil and egg mixture over squash and onion.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: brownie banana split pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs. On greased pizza pan or cookie sheet, press batter into 12-inch circle.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in juice concentrate and vanilla.
Chill thoroughly.
Spoon onto cookie circle.
Dip banana slices in lemon juice; drain well. Arrange bananas, strawberries and nuts on top.
Melt chocolate with margarine over low heat.
Drizzle over top.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over cut-up apricots.
Add sugar and butter (let cool).
Add egg, vanilla, flour, soda, salt and nuts.
I use spoon to mix.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 medium loaves.

title: lemon-buttered turnips
directions: Peel turnips and cut into 1/2-inch cubes or 2 x 1/2-inch sticks.
Cook, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Stir in margarine or butter, sliced green onion or snipped parsley and lemon juice. Season to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage stuffed french loaf
directions: Hollow bread to 1/2-inch (save crumbs).
Cook sausage, beef and onion until brown; drain.
Add 1 cup of bread crumbs, cheese and next 6 ingredients.
Spoon in loaf and replace ends. Toothpick together.
Melt butter; add garlic.
Cook 1 minute. Brush on loaf.
Wrap in foil, slightly open.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Note:
To be started the day before you plan to serve it.

title: dressing
directions: Break the bread into 1/2 to 1-inch pieces.
Put in pan and toast in oven; keep tossing around until all pieces are
dried. Melt margarine in skillet and add celery and onion (chopped fine) and pepper.
Saute until veggies are glossy and golden (15 minutes or so).
Add seasoning, water and bouillon cubes.
Let simmer 5 minutes.
Pour mixture into bread cubes and toss until all bread is moistened (mixture should not be mushy but wet enough to stick together).
Bake in buttered, shallow baking dish at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes (stir several times during baking to help dry out dressing).

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot.
Pour soup over.
Set on low setting all day.
Serve over noodles.

title: cheesy zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini.
Roll in flour, place in skillet with hot oil. Add onion, brown and drain off oil.
Top with cheese.
Serve.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips and butter.
Place in microwave for 1 minute.
Add sugar and cream.
Mix well.
Return to microwave for 3 minutes; then add nuts or peanut butter.
Put into buttered Pyrex dish and let cook.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Slice and cook potatoes.
Stir together the margarine, flour, milk, cheese and garlic salt until all are heated and blended.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over potatoes. Bake at 250° until bubbling.
Can be doubled easily.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Cover garlic with water in a small pan and boil.
Drain and cool garlic.
Peel cloves; chop and reserve.
Melt butter in a large saucepan; add onions and saute to golden brown.
Stir in garlic, then add mushrooms and zucchini; saute until tender.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, cumin and salt and pepper to taste.

title: fried squash
directions: Cook squash in water until tender; add butter, salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Cook on top of stove in skillet until liquid is reduced, being careful not to burn.
Remove from heat and cool. Add beaten eggs.
Return to heat to thicken.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls on a cookie sheet and bake.
Cream the cream cheese and add Ranch dressing.
Spread on baked crust.
Top with raw vegetables listed, all cut into small pieces; then top with cheese.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop the tomatoes.
Mix tomatoes, onions and bell peppers and cover with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Add hot peppers, sugar, vinegar and spices tied in cloth bag.
Boil until tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove spice bag. Pack tightly into clean hot pint jars. Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Yields 8 to 9 pints.

title: lorraine's calico beans
directions: Fry together the bacon, hamburger and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tuna sandwich filling(diabetic recipe)
directions: Drain tuna well, then flake into a bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Use 1/4 cup to spread on one slice of bread for an open-faced sandwich or between 2 slices of bread for a regular sandwich.

title: sweet rice balls
directions: Combine well the sweet rice flour and the salt in a large bowl.
Pour the water onto the salted sweet rice flour.
Knead that until the dough turns smooth.
Make 1/2 inch small balls. Fill 1/2 of the large Dutch pan with water and boil.
Put the rice balls into the boiling water.
(Be sure to make just one layer of balls, if not, then may stick to each other.)
After the rice balls start to float, keep boiling for 5 minutes.
Bring the balls out of the boiling water and transfer them into the cold water for a minute or two.
Remove balls out of cold water.
Roll them on cake crumbs and coconut.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook
and
crumble 1-pound bulk sausage and drain well; set aside
for later.
Beat eggs well in a large bowl and add all ingredients.
Pour	into
greased glass 9 x 13-inch dish. Refrigerate
at
least
12 hours before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini apple pie
directions: Peel and cut zucchini lengthwise in quarters.
Remove seeds; slice crosswise.
Cook zucchini until tender-crisp and drain.
In separate bowl mix zucchini, lemon juice and salt; set aside.
In another dish combine the cinnamon, cream of tartar and nutmeg; mix and add to the zucchini mixture.
Blend well all ingredients. Pour into pie crust and dot with butter.
Add the top crust and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: graduation punch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir well.
Pour mixture into a large freezer container or into 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) dishes; cover and freeze until firm.
Partially thaw mixture; break into chunks and transfer to a punch bowl.
Gently stir in ginger ale just before serving.
Garnish.
Yields 2 1/4 gallons.

title: indiana sugar cream pie
directions: Heat
milk,
sugar
and flour in saucepan over low heat until thick, but not quite boiling. Cut margarine into chunks and place in	bottom	of
pie
shell.
Pour
hot mixture over margarine
and sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon. Bake at 375° until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: praline pie
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and pecans in saucepan. Cook and stir until sugar melts and mixture bubbles vigorously.

Spread mixture in bottom of pie shell. Prepare pudding by mixing with milk according to directions. Pour over nut layer in pie shell. Allow to cool. Whip cream with vanilla and 3 tablespoons sugar. Spread over top of cooled pie and refrigerate.

title: hamburg and rice meal
directions: Brown the rice in a little butter, then put 2 cans tomato juice until rice is cooked. Simmer over low heat while you cook the hamburg and onions. After cooked, add the tomatoes and pepper. Put the rice on a plate, then add the hamburg mix. Eat with tortillas.

title: tofu hamburger
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make patties.
Make oil hot in pan. Fry patties until brown.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind onions and peppers in food processor.
Pour this over 1 pint vinegar and 1 pint of boiling water and let stand for 1/2 hour.
Drain mixture or squeeze out until dry.
Put this mixture into a kettle of 1 quart vinegar and 1 pint of sugar; let come to a boil.
Stir mixture well and put into pint jars and seal.
(The mixture will be hot.)
This is good with pinto beans!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Cream together the butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Stir in egg. Add dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Chill.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Using fork dipped in flour, flatten balls in a crisscross manner.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: mile high ice cream pie
directions: Spread vanilla ice cream on pie crust.
Spread the coffee on top.
Freeze until hard (about 2 hours).
Beat egg whites with vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until soft and glossy.
Spread meringue over ice cream to edges of pastry.
Broil 30 seconds to 1 minute until meringue is browned.
Drizzle chocolate sauce over each.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix well oil, sugar and eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients. Stir with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes at rolling boil.
Cut off heat and mix vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Blend well.
Drop by spoon on waxed paper.
Cool. Yields about 24 cookies.

title: jack-in-the-macaroni bake
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil in a large Dutch oven; stir in macaroni.
Return to a rapid boil and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
tags: shredded Monterey Jack cheese with peppers

title: pepperoni spaghetti
directions: Brown beef with onions, peppers and pepperoni.
Add sauce; simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to directions. Layer noodles on bottom of a low, flat baking dish.
Pour beef mixture on top.
Then layer white cheeses next.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and serve.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut bacon into bite sized pieces and put in heavy frying pan to cook.
Stir to keep from cooking or burning.
Pour off fat. Remove bacon and set aside.
Put potatoes in same pan.
Use enough hot water to cook potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add more water if needed.
When potatoes are cooked, add the bacon, corn and milk.
Heat almost to boiling.
Serve.
If there are leftovers, they are good reheated.
Serve with crackers or bread and tossed green salad.

title: king's arms tavern sweet potatoes(yields 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook sweet potatoes in boiling, salted water until done.
Peel and mash.

title: corn salad
directions: Bring to a boil and cook for 45 minutes.
Can put in jars and seal while hot!

title: dinner in a wrapper
directions: Slap steak on a large piece uv foil in a shallow pan...scrub steak wid lemun so steak will absorb rind flavor...spread both sides wid mustard, then gently fold foil around meat 'n brown on both sides under broiler...Take meat out 'n sprinkle wid salt 'n pepper 'n pore the juice uv a lemun over it...dab Worcestershire, sugah 'n Tabasco next...add the onions which you hav browned in buttah.
Now fold the foil over the meat 'n seal wid a double fold...bake in a 300° oven for 3 hours.
Flop it on a platter 'n serve quick like.

title: marshmallow puffs
directions: Melt caramels, butter and sweetened condensed milk in double boiler.
Leave over hot water as caramels thicken quickly. Dip marshmallows into melted caramel mixture.
Roll in Rice Krispies, coconut or chopped walnuts.

title: molded waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
In separate bowl, slowly stir cold water and lemon juice into mayonnaise and sour cream. Combine mixtures.
Chill about 2 to 3 hours or until thick.
Stir in apples, celery and walnuts.
Line 4-cup mold with mayo.
Turn Jell-O mixture into mold.
Cover tightly.
Chill overnight.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Crumble
sausage
into	a
skillet and cook until done. Place sausage
into the pie shells, then add all the remaining ingredients into a large bowl and mix well.
Pour this mixture over the
sausage
in
pie shells.	Bake in oven at 325° until golden brown (meats may vary).

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, except eggs.
Slightly beat eggs and stir into mixing bowl with first ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Excellent served with baked ham and fresh baked biscuits.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese at low speed until soft and fluffy.
Beat in confectioners sugar and milk.
Add peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: stuffed steak rolls
directions: In a skillet, saute green pepper, onion and garlic in oil until crisp-tender; remove with a slotted spoon and set aside. Combine stuffing and cheese; spoon onto the center of steaks. Roll up and tuck in ends; secure with toothpicks.

title: chicken apple spread
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: karen peck's country fried steak
directions: Flour cubed steak and brown in frying pan.
Cut potatoes and carrots; place in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper carrots and potatoes to taste.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Season meat with garlic salt, pepper, salt and lemon pepper. Layer meat in baking dish.
Slice onion and lay over meat.
Layer green beans.
Layer with soup.
Cover top with Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (until Tater Tots are cooked and brown).

title: ooey gooey cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press lightly in greased 10 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and eggs.
Pour over cake (do not mix).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Brush chicken breasts with butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Wrap in heavy foil and seal edges.
Place in shallow pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool, bone and skin. Cut into bite size pieces. There should be 2 quarts.

title: hot green casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done and break into bite size pieces. Combine salsa and soups and mix in chicken.
Cut or tear tortillas into bite-size pieces.
Grease 3-quart casserole.
Layer 1/2 of tortillas, half of soup mixture, 1/2 cheese and layer again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tangy lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, lemon flavoring and jello in a bowl. Mix until smooth.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan and bake as directed on cake box.
Mix lemonade mix and sugar. When cake is done, punch holes in top and pour lemonade mixture in holes.
Let cool and serve.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Add soda to dates and pour boiling water over; let cool. Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add to date mixture.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Grease loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate refrigerator pie
