directions: Mix these ingredients well and press in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: cinnamon rolls or doughnuts
directions: Add yeast and sugar to cooled milk.
Add enough flour to make a thin batter; let rise until light.
Cream sugar, shortening and salt.
Beat eggs well.
Add creamed mixture and well beaten eggs to the sponge.
Add flour enough to make stiff dough.
Let rise in warm place until doubled.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter and sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Roll like jelly roll and cut 1/4-inch to 1/2-inch slices.
Place cut side up on cookie sheet and let rise until double.
Always cover dough while rising. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Frost.

title: banana blueberry muffins
directions: Combine bananas, eggs, sugar and butter until well blended. Stir in blueberries and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Pour liquid mixture into dry mixture; mix until just blended.
Pour into 12 greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and water in a small bowl and set aside.
Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in Crisco until mealy.
Mix flour, yeast and milk together.
Store in an airtight container.
When ready to use, roll out as much as you want on a floured surface.
Cut and place in a greased pan.
Let rise in a warm place for 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar; work in butter.
Place on floured board and pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Do not roll.
Cut into desired shapes, squares or circles.
Bake in a 325° oven on a cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugar until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: lemon supreme apricot cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add pudding, mixed with water.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° in tube pan for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Boil all ingredients together until cooked and serve.

title: quick stuffed peppers
directions: Clean out peppers; wash and set aside.
Mix, in bowl, ground beef, rice, onions, salt, pepper and 1/2 can of tomato soup.
Roll into balls and stuff into peppers.
Pour remaining soup with added water to soup over peppers.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, margarine and 1/4 cup powdered sugar thoroughly.
Press evenly in ungreased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients except powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Pour over hot crust; bake 25 minutes longer.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bacon potato chowder
directions: Cook bacon in large saucepan over medium heat until crisp. Add onion and carrots. Cook and stir 3 minutes. Add flour; cook and stir until smooth. Stir in broth. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add hash browns; reduce heat to medium-low. Simmer 6 to 8 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in milk; cook 2 to 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated. (Do Not Boil.)

title: brownies
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Blend with fork the eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, nuts and raisins.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for exactly 30 minutes (do not overbake).
Cut into squares.

title: heavenly seven-layer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large container (an old cooler works great).
Place roasts, steaks, etc., in cooler and marinate for 12 to 24 hours, prior to cooking.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend and refrigerate.
Makes over 2 quarts.

title: stewed tomatoes supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook.
Serve hot or cold.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, salt, dry mustard and poppy seed; mix well.
Add onion and vinegar.
As you are mixing these ingredients, begin adding oil in a slow trickle.
Stir constantly while you are adding oil.
Dressing may be kept in refrigerator for a week or more.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour batter into hot skillet.
Will make 8 to 10 medium-size pancakes.

title: hawaiian cheese ball
directions: Pour crushed drained pineapple into paper towels and blot. Make sure to drain pineapple well.
Mix all ingredients together and form into ball.
Roll in pecans until cheese ball is covered well.
Refrigerate for a few hours before serving.

title: granny's baby food cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into prepared Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, or until done.

title: kung pao chicken
directions: Mix wine vinegar, soy and sugar. Coat chicken with cornstarch. Stir-fry for 5 to 7 minutes and remove. Stir-fry onion, garlic, red pepper and ginger for 1 minute. Add wine vinegar mixture, chicken and peanuts and stir. Serve over rice.

title: chicken log
directions: Mix cheese, mayo, lemon juice, salt, ginger, pepper and pepper sauce.
Stir in chicken, eggs and green pepper.
Shape into log, 8 x 12 inches.
Wrap in plastic wrap; refrigerate about 4 hours. Top with toasted sesame seed.
Serve with crackers and/or bread rounds.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken consomme
directions: Heat all ingredients, except chicken, to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Strain.
Stir in chicken and heat through.

title: appetizer cheese fondue
directions: In small chafing dish or fondue pot over low heat, heat undiluted soup, wine, chives and Worcestershire until hot and bubbly, stirring occasionally.
Cut bread into 1 1/2-inch chunks. To serve, let guests spear bread with fondue forks and dip into hot mixture.
Makes 3 cups.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: Heat and stir sugar, syrup and water in 3-quart heavy pan until sugar dissolves.
When syrup boils, put in butter.
Add peanuts.
Cook until cracking stage.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Pour on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: mesquite bean muffins
directions: Mesquite Flour:
Gather mature beans, thoroughly dry them in a low oven (140° to 150°).
Grind in a blender the whole bean!
Sift flour to remove unground parts.
Store in a tight container and refrigerate if possible because it is very appealing to insects.

title: impossible chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Mix all ingredients, except whipped cream, on high speed for 1 minute. Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: brunch eggs(breakfast - brunch)
directions: Beat eggs and milk together and cook over low heat with 1/2 cup margarine until soft and still quite moist.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat until steaming and spicy. Serve very hot. Serves 12.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs and bananas. Beat good. Add salt, baking soda, flour, vanilla and nuts. Mix well. Put into greased loaf pan or you can use 2 small pans. Bake 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: venison steak and tomatoes
directions: Brown steaks in oil in skillet.
Place in baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange veggies over steaks.
Combine catsup and steak sauce. Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: grandma gin's honey cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, egg and honey.
Mix flour with dry ingredients.
Add slowly to mixture.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls onto buttered and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured bread pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix everything together for a few minutes, or until thoroughly mixed.
Store in airtight container in a dry place.

title: bread pudding with whiskey sauce
directions: Scald milk.
Put bread cubes in large bowl.
Pour milk over bread cubes.
Cool.
Add butter, sugar, eggs, salt, raisins and cinnamon; mix well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put casserole in a pan of hot water (1-inch deep).
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until knife inserted into pudding comes out clean.
Serve warm with Whiskey Sauce.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip together.
Then add rest of ingredients.

title: up north mud pie
directions: Pour milk into large mixing bowl.
Add pie filling.
Mix instant coffee.
Beat with a wire whisk for 1 minute; let stand for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, for about 2 hours.
Top with fudge sauce and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans in the bottom of a baking dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over beans. Slice cheese and place on top.
Cover with crushed cracker crumbs. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix
all
together, place in baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cube melted butter and 1 cup fresh bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add refried beans. Mix together onion, tomato, lettuce, cheese and avocado.
Mix with meat mixture.
Add French dressing.
Add taco sauce.
Just before serving, add Doritos.

title: parmesan vegetable toss
directions: Marinate vegetables and onion in mayonnaise, sugar, Parmesan and basil overnight.
Before serving, add bacon, lettuce and croutons.
This is a very large salad.

title: hopping john
directions: Boil peas in salted water until tender.
Add peas and 1 cup of pea liquid to rice, bacon with grease and onion.
Put in rice steamer or double boiler and cook 1 hour or until rice is thoroughly done.
Serves 8.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: All in one bowl, blend ingredients 2 minutes.
Pour into 1 large Bundt pan or 2 small pans and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes, invert on rack.
Make orange or lemon glaze with sifted powdered sugar and either lemon or orange juice.
Poke holes in cake with toothpick and pour glaze over, dripping down the sides of the cake.

title: hershey's fudge
directions: Stir and cook over high heat until forms a soft ball.
Set pan in cold water to reduce to about 110°.
Add butter and vanilla and beat and pour into buttered pan.

title: creamed onions
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt and chives.
Add cream.
Cook until bubbly, about 3 minutes.
Spoon cooked onions into a dish. Pour sauce over onions.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Ready to serve.

title: blackened seasoning powder
directions: Heat heavy
medium
skillet (preferably cast-iron) over medium-high heat.
Add
all
ingredients,
except paprika, and stir until aromatic
and beginning to darken, about 3 minutes. Grind finely in
spice grinder or in mortar and pestle.
Blend in paprika.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Put nuts in bottom and up sides of pan.
Mix cake mix and instant pudding.
Add water, extract, oil and eggs.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Leave in pan; have glaze ready.

title: bread muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased muffin pan and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: crowd pleasing vegetable bake
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Combine cream-style corn, drained whole corn, cheese and soup.
Fold in cooked vegetables and mushrooms.
Put mixture in 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter; sprinkle top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let it stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Save broth, adding 1 tablespoon margarine to broth.
Dice chicken into small pieces; put in pie shell.

title: chicken and broccoli au gratin
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion until transparent. Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, curry powder and pepper. Drain mushrooms; reserve liquid.
Add water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Gradually stir into flour mixture in skillet.
Blend in evaporated milk until smooth.
Add mushrooms.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sauce begins to thicken.
Arrange chicken and broccoli.
Use 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over; top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: goode dip
directions: Heat soup and jello.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate. Serve with corn chips.

title: yummy frozen dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch pan and freeze.
Serve frozen or thawed.

title: clothesline chili sauce
directions: Mix tomatoes, red peppers and green peppers with salt.
Put in colander and let drain overnight.
Boil and also let stand overnight 1 quart vinegar and 1 small box (2 ounces) mustard seed.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix flour with Crisco.
Add other ingredients.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake at 425° for 10 or 12 minutes.

title: low calorie dessert
directions: Mix sugar-free drink mix with water as directed on package. Mix well and bring to boil.
Cool.
Add unflavored gelatin and mix until dissolved.
Pour into mold and chill in refrigerator until firm.
Makes 4 servings.
One serving equals negligible calories and free exchange.

title: beef-broccoli pie
directions: Roll one package of rolls into square; place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Fill with meat; slice cheese on top.
Roll out second package of rolls and make top crust.
Cut slits; brush with milk. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cover last 20 minutes, if too brown.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Prepare a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on the box.
Add the instant pudding to the cake batter. Pour into pan.
Arrange peaches on top of batter.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and juice.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in the pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: garlic cheese croutons
directions: Combine powdered bouillon, butter, garlic, and parmesan cheese.
Add cubed bread and toss gently.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes or until brown.
Serve with salad or soup.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Put pineapple juice, sherbet, and ice cream in a large mixing bowl;
blend thoroughly with electric mixer at low speed.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add salt.
Stir in flour and mix until well blended.
Add chocolate syrup, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Turn into well-greased and floured 9-inch pan. Smooth top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until done. Cool in pan, but loosen edges.
Cut into squares.

title: icing
directions: Mix all ingredients. Good on any flavor cake.

title: potato casserole
directions: Break apart potatoes; spread in a 2 1/2-quart casserole; mix onions, garlic salt, soup and sour cream; spread on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle on cheese; top with cornflake crumbs.
Drizzle butter over top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, vanilla and sugar, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until center is done.

title: ice cream muffins
directions: Mix and roll in marble size balls.
Put 3 balls in each cup of a muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: walnut torte
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until thick and lemon colored. Sift flour and baking powder.
Add slowly with chopped nuts to egg mixture.
Add vanilla;
beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into first
mixture.
Bake
in
two well-greased 9-inch round pans at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.	Cool and remove.
Ice with Custard Frosting.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread refried beans on a large dinner plate.
Cover with sour cream, spoon on picante sauce, then layer chopped tomato, lettuce, onions, cheese.

title: pot roast
directions: Season roast and dredge in flour.
Put oil in Dutch oven. Brown the roast to desired color.
Pour off excess oil.
Add 2 cups water.
Cook under a lid until almost done.
Peel and quarter up potatoes into roast.
Chop onion into roast.
Scrape carrots and cut into about 1-inch chunks.
Put a lid on Dutch oven and cook until vegetables are done.
Serve over rice with hot rolls or biscuits.

title: blueberry crumb dessert
directions: Mix the oats, flour and brown sugar.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Line bottom of an 8-inch square pan with oatmeal mixture, reserving 3/4 cup for topping.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and simmer about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour into crust.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve topped with whipped cream or ice cream.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pizza chili
directions: In large soup pot, combine chuck and onions.
Cook until chuck is no longer pink and the onion is tender.
Add chili powder and stir.
Add pork and beans, pizza sauce, and water.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to medium low.
Cook for about 10 to 15 minutes, adding water, if needed.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Mix powdered sugar, cracker crumbs, peanut butter, and margarine until blended.
Scrape into ungreased 13x9 pan and press into an even layer.
Spread melted chocolate over top. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Tastes just like Reeses Cups!

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and cut into small pieces.
Add mayonnaise and 3/4 cup of the Parmesan cheese.
Mix thoroughly. Spread into a small shallow pan.
Sprinkle the remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 1/2 hour, uncovered, at 350° or until hot.
Serve warm with Triscuits.

title: feijoada latin style
directions: Cover beans with cold water and soak overnight, or cover them with boiling water and let stand for 2 hours.
Drain.

title: polish "lazy man's pierogies"
directions: Dice and fry bacon.
Drain and set aside.
Dice onions and brown lightly in margarine (bacon grease may be used instead of margarine which gives a delicious flavor and keeps noodles moist). Add sauerkraut to onions.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Cook noodles.
Combine noodles, sauerkraut, onions, soup, bacon and mushrooms.
Mix thoroughly.
Freezes well.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix in a heavy 2-quart buttered saucepan, sugar, butter, milk, marshmallows and salt.
Cook over medium heat (stir constantly) until it comes to a full boil.
Continue cooking and stirring for 5 minutes.
Take off heat.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread over cooled crust and add:

title: macaroni pizza
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Beat together milk, 1 teaspoon Parmesan cheese and salt.
Blend into macaroni and spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add bits of raw hamburger.
Sprinkle green pepper, onions and mushrooms.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: *To toast:
Spread onto shallow pan and toast at 350°, just until oatmeal begins to change color, 5 to 10 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: pork or chicken and rice
directions: Chop pork or chicken and cook in small amount of oil until brown.
Drain.
Pour tomato sauce over browned meat, onion and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over fried rice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 pan.
Blend in graham cracker crumbs and pat evenly over the bottom.
In a bowl, beat 2 sticks butter, eggs and sugar at high speed for 15 minutes.
Carefully spread this blend over crust.
Layer sliced bananas over the mix.
Spread Cool Whip on top of fruit layer.
Sprinkle on nuts and place cherries on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: rabbit pot pie
directions: Heat margarine in large frying pan. Add onion and green pepper.
Cook 5 minutes over low heat. Blend in flour and cook until bubbly.
Pour in broth gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and smooth, stirring frequently.
Add seasoning.
Add meat and vegetables to gravy and heat.
Pour mixture into pie crust. Place top crust on and cut slits for steam to escape. Bake at 425° until crust browns and sauce bubbles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli well, drain.
Put in large mixing bowl.
Add cream of celery soup and cream of mushroom soup, onion (diced) and margarine (melted).
Mix together well, then add crackers (crushed) with cheese.

title: apple dessert
directions: Slice apples in casserole.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; spread over apples.
Beat egg thoroughly.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, softened butter, flour and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
May double recipe in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Combine 1/3 of cake mix with 1 egg and margarine in bowl, mixing well.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine remaining cake mix, 3 eggs, brown sugar, corn syrup and vanilla in bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes with electric mixer at medium speed.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with pecans. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes longer, or until light brown.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Stir in cereal and chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Approximate yield:
5 dozen.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar to	dark brown in skillet.	Add hot water and 1 cup sugar;
boil
to	dissolve,
about 3 to 5 minutes.
Add salt and butter.

title: frozen cabbage slaw(yields about 8 cups)
directions: Make a syrup using the vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
After sugar is dissolved, boil 5 minutes; cool. Combine shredded cabbage and salt; mixing well.
Let stand 1 hour. Squeeze out cabbage and discard liquid.
Add shredded carrots and red and green peppers.
Add cold syrup.
(Syrup must be cold or cabbage will turn dark.)
Immediately pack into glass jars of desired size, leaving some space on top for mixture to expand as it freezes.
Cover tightly and freeze.
A pint jar transferred from freezer to refrigerator will defrost in about 6 hours.
This recipe freezes well for over a year.
It is easy to multiply the recipe for that extra cabbage from your garden or a good buy at the market.

title: flag dessert
directions: Slice 1 cup of strawberries and set aside.
Slice the remaining strawberries in half and set aside.
Line the bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish with cake slices.
Top with 1 cup sliced strawberries, 1 cup of blueberries and all the Cool Whip.
Place the remaining strawberries and blueberries on Cool Whip to create a flag design.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 15 servings.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Make pastry for 9-inch pie.
You can use already made pie crust (unbaked).
Mix flour, sugar and salt and sprinkle small amount in pastry-lined pan (1/4 cup).
Combine remaining sugar mixture with rhubarb and berries.
Put in pie pan and dot with butter.
Put top pastry on pie.
Cut a few slits for steam to escape.
Bake in 425° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in mixer bowl; blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, candied cherries and pecans.
Form into 2 rolls, each 2 inches in diameter and 8 inches long.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap and chill for several hours or overnight.
Slice 1/4 inch thick and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 minutes or until edges are golden. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat the sugar, flour and eggs well; add to hot milk in double boiler.
Mix
well.
When
it starts to coat the spoon, remove from
water
and
beat well.
Add marshmallows and beat well.
Add vanilla flavoring and chill.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut an acorn squash in half and remove seeds.
Cover bottom of baking dish with boiling water.
Place squash cut side down in water and bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then turn cup side up. Place 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons Log Cabin syrup and 1/2 to 1 tablespoon butter in center of each half.
Sprinkle with salt. Continue baking about 30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 2 servings.

title: happy hour mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Wash caps and brush with melted butter.
Combine soft butter, garlic and cheese.
Mix well.
Add wine, soy sauce, onion dip and Fritos to make a paste.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Place on baking sheet and broil 3 minutes, until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a heavy skillet and cook until it reaches soft ball stage; then add peanut butter and butter. Remove from heat and beat by hand until it starts to thicken. Pour onto a buttered platter.
Chill and cut.

title: cooked pecans
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Mix everything together in white of egg (mix well).
Spread on cookie sheet.
Cook for 1 hour at 225°.
Stir 3 times during the hour.

title: apple and banana pie
directions: Combine apples, bananas and lemon juice; let stand 10 minutes. Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in oleo until crumbly.
Arrange fruit in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Serve with whipped cream.
Good without cream.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Let cream cheese and margarine stand at room temperature until softened. Beat all ingredients until creamy.

title: barbecue pork spareribs
directions: Brown ribs on flat sheet with salt and pepper at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn.
In saucepan, cook rest of ingredients.
Put browned ribs in big pot or 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Pour sauce over ribs; best if sauce covers ribs.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick doughnuts
directions: Separate biscuits.
Press into flat round circles.
Cut a hole in center.
Heat oil in small kettle.
Drop biscuits, 2 at a time, into hot oil, turning once.
Fry to golden brown.
Remove and place on paper towel.
As soon as they drain, combine sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Roll doughnuts in this while they are still warm.
Continue to do so with doughnut holes and remaining doughnuts.
May use sugar and cinnamon to your taste.
You may also dip in melted butter before frying.

title: tater swiss omelet
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan.
Add potatoes and fry until brown.
Place in 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with cooked and crumbled bacon.
Stir together egg yolks, mushrooms and cheese.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold cheese mixture into whites.
Pour over bacon.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Serves 6.

title: quick fudge frosting
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Remove from heat; let cool.
In medium bowl, combine butter, sugar, salt and 3 tablespoons hot cream.
With wooden spoon, beat until mixture is smooth.
Add chocolate; continue beating until frosting is thick enough to spread.
Add vanilla.

title: fruit slush mix
directions: Heat sugar and water in a medium saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and pineapple juice. Mix well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Tear chicken into pieces.
Place in casserole dish.
Layer vegetables and soup.
Combine melted butter with flour and put on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: In a bowl, mix crumbs, pecans, brown sugar and cloves.
Stir in butter.
Press over bottom and halfway up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook until it forms a hard ball in cold water, then fold in egg whites until it gets thick.
Add pecans and pour into a baking pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: rice casserole #1
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: yorkville torte
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes; cool.
Blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip and spread on crust.
Cook pudding with 3 cups milk until thick and put on top of cream cheese.
Mix while still hot.
When cool, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream and soup; reserve 1/3 of the mixture.
Mix chicken, olives, chilies, 1/2 the cheese and the 2/3 remainder of soup mixture.
Fill and roll tortillas.
Put into a greased pan. Top with remaining 1/3 soup mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in an iron skillet.
Add rest of ingredients except cereal.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies. Stir well.
Cool until you can handle, then form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: bubble solution
directions: Mix gently and allow to sit for a while.

title: italian steak
directions: Brown onions and green pepper in oil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Blend in other ingredients.
Put steak in roaster and pour all over. Bake covered 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 250°.

title: slush party punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil; add jello and mix well.
Cool, then add frozen orange juice and large can of pineapple juice, water and extract.
Freeze.

title: cuban pork
directions: Cut 1-inch deep slits in roast.
Insert whole sections garlic. Add Key lime juice, oregano, salt and pepper.
Pour over roast. Baste throughout the day every 2 hours.
Bake in oven or grill desired time for size of roast.
Baste throughout cooking time with juice mixture.

title: batter fried fish
directions: Cut fish into serving size pieces, in a bowl.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Drop egg yolk in center and add water and shortening.
Mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Bring sauce to boil and pour over sliced yams.
Bake in 400° oven until candied, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: nina's molasses cookies with jelly
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add egg and molasses. Stir together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and ginger. Add to molasses mixture; mix well.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Make into balls and flatten with wooden mallet dipped in flour.
Fill centers with currant jelly.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Good luck!

title: cheese cake
directions: Crush graham crackers very fine.
Add melted butter and mix. Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, saving 1/2 cup mixture for topping.
Add sugar to softened cream cheese.
Mix well and set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water and chill until syrup consistency.
Whip chilled milk in large bowl and add lemon juice and whip.
Add gelatin mixture to milk mixture; beat well.
Add cream cheese mixture to milk mixture about 1/4 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour mixture into pan; sprinkle top with graham cracker mixture.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs slightly with a rotary beater or fork.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in dark corn syrup and melted butter or margarine.
Mix well.

title: crispy shortbread cookies
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until smooth. Add vanilla and flour, beating well.
Stir in corn flakes.
Shape dough into a long roll, 2-inches in diameter; gently roll in pecans. Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight or until firm.
Let roll stand at room temperature about 10 minutes. Cut dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool on wire racks.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: apple rings
directions: Mix sugars, margarine and water together in a large baking dish.
Put in a 400° oven until bubbly. Sift flour and salt together. Cut shortening into flour. Add the water gradually until it holds together.
Roll out dough and cut into a rectangle about 10 x 12-inches.
Chop 4 cups apples.
Place on dough. Sprinkle with sugar if apples are tart.
Roll up pastry and slice into 1-inch pieces.
Place in hot syrup. Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake 45 minutes or until done in a 350° oven.

title: ice cube pickles
directions: Put all vegetables into a pan.
Sprinkle salt over all.
Cover with ice cubes.
Let stand until ice melts.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and can.

title: crispy chicken stir-fry(weight watchers)
directions: Place baking mix and pepper in gallon size sealable plastic bag.
In shallow bowl, lightly beat egg whites; add chicken cubes and stir to coat.
Place chicken in bag; seal bag, squeezing out excess air.
Shake until chicken is coated.
Remove from bag; sprinkle with any remaining mixture and set aside.

title: chicken and okra gumbo
directions: Cook chicken about 45 minutes.
Remove chicken and reserve broth.
Bone and cube chicken; set aside.
In an 8-quart kettle combine oil and flour until smooth.
Cook over medium-high heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium; cook and stir about 5 more minutes, until mixture is reddish-brown (color of a penny).
Turn the heat to high; stir in 2 cups of reserved broth, mixing well.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add onions, celery, green pepper and garlic; cook and stir for 5 minutes.
Add chicken, tomatoes, okra, bay leaves, basil, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: lemon drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat.
Add extracts.
Sift dry ingredients together; blend into creamed mixture.
Chill in refrigerator. Roll into balls, then roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: peanut butter gluppies
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan over low heat.
In large bowl, put graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Pour melted margarine over mixture.
Mix well.
Add peanut butter to these ingredients, mixing well.
Press mixture onto a 9 x 13-inch baking sheet.

title: spiced chicken nuggets
directions: Put last 7 ingredients into a plastic bag and shake well. Place foil over a baking sheet.
Dip chicken pieces in butter and shake a few at a time in the bag.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken breast scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut chicken breast into bite size pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add the garlic, scallions, parsley, dill, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Pour the mixture over the chicken pieces.
Bake 10 minutes.
Turn over chicken pieces and bake another 10 minutes.
Turn over to broil and put chicken under broiler for 3 to 4 minutes or until lightly brown. Serve over rice or spaghetti to sop up garlic sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mighty mo sauce
directions: Combine ketchup, chilli sauce, A.1. sauce, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and finely chopped sweet pickles and add to sauce mixture mayonnaise. Stir until well blended. Makes 2 1/2 cups. Great on hamburgers.

title: del bars
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs and coconut; set aside.
Mix the eggs, 2 sticks butter, sugar, cocoa and vanilla together and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add to crumb mixture.
Butter a large 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet and pat crumb mixture into pan. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar; beat well.
Mix top or crumb mixture.
Spread melted butter and chocolate chips on top of the entire mixture.
Chill until hard.
Remove from refrigerator about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: mark's green chili stew from chapel hill, north carolina
directions: Heat oil in a 4-quart pot.
Add pork; cook until lightly browned.
Add onions and garlic.
Add flour; stir for 2 minutes. Add tomatoes, green chilies, jalapeno, salt and sugar.
Mix and add chicken broth.
Lower heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, until meat is tender.
Serve with warm flour tortillas.
Serves 6.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Combine
ingredients in electric skillet.
Set temperature at 300°
and
stir
briskly
until
the
sugar
and water mixture is all absorbed and looks crystallized.
Spread evenly on a
cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20 minutes stirring 2 or 3
times. Watch
carefully
as peanuts will burn easily in oven.
Cool on foil.
Store in glass jar in refrigerator.

title: skillet potatoes
directions: In large skillet combine all prepared ingredients and cover. Cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender, about 45 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray. Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake about an hour until meat is no longer pink.
Drain immediately.

title: cherry bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, milk and dried ingredients.
Place half of batter in a jelly roll pan.
Cover with cherry pie mix (add a little almond flavoring, if desired, to filling).
Spoon the rest of the batter over the top.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, water, evaporated milk and rice in a large pan and bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook for 30 minutes.
Add raisins and continue cooking for approximately 10 minutes or until thick and creamy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: meat cakes
directions: Mix ingredients and form into thick cakes.
Coat cakes with flour.
Brown both sides in hot oil, reduce heat and simmer in oil 15 minutes on each side.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all the ingredients and spread in a buttered pan.
Cook at 350° until brown.
Use a large enough pan to spread thin.

title: corn dogs
directions: Dry hot dogs with paper towel.
Mix ingredients.
Roll hot dogs in mixture and drop into hot oil or shortening.
Cook until golden brown.
Remove and let cool slightly.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 egg, oleo, and pie spice until crumbly.
Press in bottom of 15x10 jelly roll pan.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk, then remaining 2 eggs, pumpkin, remaining pie spice, and salt, mix well.
Pour over crust; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 30 - 35 minutes or until set.
Cool. Chill; cut into bars.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 48 bars.

title: quick-n-easy one dish casserole
directions: Crumble and cook sausage until brown; drain on paper towel. Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Cook Stove Top dressing according to package directions.
Place stuffing on bottom of large square Pyrex dish.
Place cooked sausage on top of stuffing.
Place broccoli on top of sausage.
Sprinkle generously with Kraft shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: company potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Boil until tender, drain.
Beat softened cream cheese and sour cream at medium speed until well blended. Add hot potatoes gradually, beating constantly.
Add onion, mayonnaise, garlic powder, salt and pepper, still beating until potatoes are light and fluffy.
Put into a 2 quart casserole, sprinkle on parmesan cheese, dot with butter and sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 325 degrees for 25-30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: patti's chili
directions: Brown ground beef.

Add garlic, onion, green pepper, celery, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, oregano and salt and pepper. Cook about 10 minutes. Add beans, tomatoes and paste. Simmer about 45 minutes. Delicious with crusty French bread and tossed salad. All quantities may be adjusted to your taste.

title: hawaiian luau
directions: Crush wafers and blend with margarine.
Press on bottom of large serving dish.
Slice bananas and layer over wafers.
Mix lemon juice and condensed milk until thick.
Pour over bananas. Drain pineapple and layer over milk mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut, then nuts and cherries on top.

title: easy green punch
directions: Mix liquid ingredients in punch bowl.
Float lime sherbet on top.
Makes about 30 servings.

title: tortellini and vegetable salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water until completely cool.
In medium bowl, blend vegetable recipe soup mix, mayonnaise, oil, lemon, basil, parsley and pepper.
Toss with tortellini, green onions and tomato; chill.
Makes about 4 cups of salad.

title: swedish "brownies"
directions: Mix all ingredients except chopped almonds together in a greased 8 inch square pan.	Sprinkle chopped almonds and coarse sugar (I use granulated on the boat) on top.
Bake at 325 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: zeppole(st. joseph's day cream puffs)
directions: Set out 9-inch round layer cake pan.
